1
00:01:15,570 --> 00:01:18,448
Miss, we'll be landing soon.

2
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:20,492
Would you like a glass
of the same wine?

3
00:01:21,868 --> 00:01:23,745
No, that's okay.

4
00:01:24,329 --> 00:01:26,164
By the way,

5
00:01:26,206 --> 00:01:27,707
I'm Korean.

6
00:01:27,749 --> 00:01:30,085
Is that so? My apologies.

7
00:01:30,127 --> 00:01:31,503
Have a comfortable flight.

8
00:01:46,977 --> 00:01:52,482
The chairman's main
business is real estate.

9
00:01:52,983 --> 00:01:58,280
He owns a ton of land in Korea
and has investments here too.

10
00:01:58,321 --> 00:02:02,284
You know, he's one of those
people born into money.

11
00:02:02,325 --> 00:02:04,953
The filthy rich ones.

12
00:02:08,248 --> 00:02:09,957
How am I supposed to trust them?

13
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:12,502
You should have considered
my opinion too.

14
00:02:13,879 --> 00:02:16,381
These are totally
different circumstances.

15
00:02:16,423 --> 00:02:17,299
I don't get it.

16
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,758
Just do whatever you want.

17
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:35,358
We've calmed him down with sedatives,

18
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:38,778
but he hasn't stopped
crying since birth.

19
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:42,741
All top doctors here have examined him,

20
00:02:42,782 --> 00:02:46,077
but he's medically sound.

21
00:02:46,119 --> 00:02:48,538
So we've heard.

22
00:02:55,003 --> 00:02:58,381
My apologies, but could we
have the room to ourselves?

23
00:02:58,423 --> 00:02:59,591
Pardon?

24
00:03:39,631 --> 00:03:42,134
There must be others with the
same condition in your family.

25
00:03:42,175 --> 00:03:43,468
His father...

26
00:03:44,803 --> 00:03:45,803
and his grandfather.

27
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,273
Is she talking about
Ji-yong and his father?

28
00:03:56,314 --> 00:03:58,108
<i>Those expressions...</i>

29
00:03:58,150 --> 00:03:59,025
Yes.

30
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,735
<i>...changing from suspicion</i>

31
00:04:01,653 --> 00:04:02,988
<i>to shock.</i>

32
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:11,246
<i>They live in the light and
look towards bright spaces.</i>

33
00:04:14,249 --> 00:04:17,836
<i>Bright lights are needed
in the world for us to see.</i>

34
00:04:18,962 --> 00:04:23,341
<i>And people only believe in
things they can see and touch.</i>

35
00:04:27,012 --> 00:04:28,638
<i>A world with bright lights.</i>

36
00:04:31,099 --> 00:04:33,185
<i>And the back side of it.</i>

37
00:04:39,983 --> 00:04:43,945
<i>People have known of the beings
living in the darkness for a long time</i>

38
00:04:45,030 --> 00:04:46,656
<i>and have called them by many names.</i>

39
00:04:47,657 --> 00:04:51,286
<i>Ghosts, devils, goblins, ghouls...</i>

40
00:04:51,912 --> 00:04:55,832
<i>These beings constantly
envy and long for the light,</i>

41
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:57,793
<i>and just occasionally</i>

42
00:04:58,668 --> 00:05:00,504
<i>would cross the line.</i>

43
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,510
<i>That's when people ask for me.</i>

44
00:05:10,722 --> 00:05:11,722
<i>Yin and Yang.</i>

45
00:05:12,474 --> 00:05:14,059
<i>Science and superstition.</i>

46
00:05:15,185 --> 00:05:16,853
<i>I exist between them.</i>

47
00:05:18,188 --> 00:05:21,024
<i>I am Shaman Lee Hwa-rim.</i>

48
00:05:21,066 --> 00:05:22,901
My wife told me you'd be coming.

49
00:05:23,527 --> 00:05:24,694
I'm Park Ji-yong.

50
00:05:35,664 --> 00:05:39,334
My brother committed
suicide in the mental ward.

51
00:05:40,377 --> 00:05:41,545
Then it began with me,

52
00:05:42,462 --> 00:05:43,462
and now...

53
00:05:45,173 --> 00:05:47,259
my newborn son.

54
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:52,264
When I close my eyes, I hear screaming.

55
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,891
And a sensation of being choked.

56
00:05:55,851 --> 00:05:59,020
Firstborns and tainted blood...

57
00:06:00,355 --> 00:06:02,774
Normally, genetics
are initially blamed,

58
00:06:02,816 --> 00:06:05,856
then the land their house is built on,
and finally, they move to a new place.

59
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:07,319
Shadow...

60
00:06:08,155 --> 00:06:11,158
I saw a shadow here
as soon as I arrived.

61
00:06:11,199 --> 00:06:13,368
It's pressing down on its descendants.

62
00:06:14,703 --> 00:06:18,290
It's likely the shadow
of your grandfather.

63
00:06:18,915 --> 00:06:19,916
My grandfather?

64
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:24,212
We refer to it as the Grave's Calling.

65
00:06:25,589 --> 00:06:30,051
Simply put, it's one of your ancestors
throwing a tantrum in their grave.

66
00:06:31,261 --> 00:06:32,220
Are you certain?

67
00:06:32,262 --> 00:06:34,639
Yes, 100%.

68
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:40,896
Then what do I have to do?

69
00:06:42,856 --> 00:06:44,733
You've got to spend
money and hire people.

70
00:06:44,774 --> 00:06:48,653
I can't do this on my own.
We'll have to work with experts.

71
00:06:50,113 --> 00:06:51,615
Damn it.

72
00:06:52,908 --> 00:06:55,452
Why are they the only
ones I can think of?

73
00:07:23,355 --> 00:07:26,441
- Exhumation!
- Exhumation!

74
00:07:29,903 --> 00:07:32,322
How dare you stare at your
ancestor's awakening!

75
00:07:33,156 --> 00:07:34,449
I'm sorry.

76
00:07:34,491 --> 00:07:36,409
Come on, let's go.

77
00:07:38,328 --> 00:07:40,121
- One, two, three!
- Three!

78
00:07:50,881 --> 00:07:52,341
No sign of water.

79
00:07:53,217 --> 00:07:56,554
I'm sorry for waking you up.

80
00:07:57,847 --> 00:07:59,140
It's very clean.

81
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:01,934
Nice and fragrant.

82
00:08:01,976 --> 00:08:05,104
This coffin is stuffed.

83
00:08:05,646 --> 00:08:07,022
Man, oh man.

84
00:08:07,773 --> 00:08:13,070
I told them not to put any
metals inside for her sake.

85
00:08:15,531 --> 00:08:16,866
Chairman Kim.

86
00:08:16,907 --> 00:08:21,704
I've settled on the plots for your
mother and ancestors, haven't I?

87
00:08:21,745 --> 00:08:23,622
Yes, that's correct.

88
00:08:23,664 --> 00:08:28,627
And you're all healthy and
business is good, yes?

89
00:08:28,669 --> 00:08:30,337
Yes, thanks to you.

90
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:33,841
No matter how I look at it,

91
00:08:34,467 --> 00:08:39,262
this is one of the finest plots
I've seen in my 40-year career.

92
00:08:39,305 --> 00:08:42,266
It's got all the five
elements right here, see?

93
00:08:42,308 --> 00:08:43,517
It really does, all right?

94
00:08:44,602 --> 00:08:47,480
I really gave you a good deal.

95
00:08:47,521 --> 00:08:48,606
Right, I'm sure.

96
00:08:49,815 --> 00:08:51,567
So set aside your worry.

97
00:08:52,526 --> 00:08:54,528
Do the right thing and re-bury her.

98
00:08:55,529 --> 00:08:58,407
It must be the right
call if you say so.

99
00:08:58,449 --> 00:09:01,911
But why does she keep
showing up in my kids' dreams?

100
00:09:01,952 --> 00:09:03,954
Even my wife said
she's been seeing her.

101
00:09:05,539 --> 00:09:06,540
Mr. Ko!

102
00:09:07,374 --> 00:09:08,876
What's taking so long?

103
00:09:08,918 --> 00:09:10,461
I'm starving.

104
00:09:10,503 --> 00:09:13,506
I'm hungry too, and so is she.

105
00:09:13,547 --> 00:09:16,342
Look, someone shrouded
her without checking.

106
00:09:16,383 --> 00:09:17,527
- Does the count look good?
- Yes.

107
00:09:17,551 --> 00:09:18,551
Good.

108
00:09:33,275 --> 00:09:35,277
Someone has the old lady's teeth.

109
00:09:38,030 --> 00:09:40,157
Who took the old lady's dentures?

110
00:09:52,253 --> 00:09:55,714
Did you take Grandma's teeth?

111
00:09:56,423 --> 00:09:57,466
Sang-hyun.

112
00:09:57,508 --> 00:10:00,344
The thing in your closet,
was that her teeth?

113
00:10:00,386 --> 00:10:02,346
Why would you...

114
00:10:02,847 --> 00:10:05,015
All her stuff was burned,

115
00:10:05,975 --> 00:10:07,476
and now she's gone.

116
00:10:08,644 --> 00:10:09,937
Dad.

117
00:10:09,979 --> 00:10:12,189
I just wanted something
that was hers...

118
00:10:12,231 --> 00:10:15,109
Kid, your grandma says she's hungry.

119
00:10:15,151 --> 00:10:16,193
Let's return it to her.

120
00:10:16,235 --> 00:10:18,070
What about me then?

121
00:10:18,112 --> 00:10:20,447
What do I remember her by?

122
00:10:21,073 --> 00:10:23,409
There's nothing left of her.

123
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:24,577
Sang-hyun, right?

124
00:10:25,286 --> 00:10:30,958
Sang-hyun, your grandma
will always be by your side.

125
00:10:39,592 --> 00:10:40,592
<i>Bloodline.</i>

126
00:10:41,886 --> 00:10:44,388
<i>People that remain tied even in death.</i>

127
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:48,434
<i>A group that shares the same genes
and physical and mental attributes.</i>

128
00:10:49,894 --> 00:10:53,731
<i>When a person's body finishes its
cycle, it turns into dirt and earth.</i>

129
00:10:54,815 --> 00:10:58,819
<i>As we drink from that
dirt and walk on that earth,</i>

130
00:10:58,861 --> 00:11:03,866
<i>we live, die, and are
reborn in a cyclical nature.</i>

131
00:11:03,908 --> 00:11:08,954
<i>In other words, the dirt and
earth connect and cycle everything.</i>

132
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:13,584
<i>All the skeptics can fuck off.</i>

133
00:11:13,626 --> 00:11:17,922
<i>To the top 1%, feng shui
is a religion and science.</i>

134
00:11:20,508 --> 00:11:21,801
<i>And I'm a feng shui expert.</i>

135
00:11:22,927 --> 00:11:26,847
<i>I find and plot the land
for the dead and the living.</i>

136
00:11:26,889 --> 00:11:29,850
<i>I am Geomancer Kim Sang-duk.</i>

137
00:11:29,892 --> 00:11:32,478
<i>Noble Funeral Home</i>

138
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:35,481
<i>Many domestic companies see
the current economic situation</i>

139
00:11:35,523 --> 00:11:37,107
<i>as a prolonged downturn.</i>

140
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:39,276
<i>According to the findings...</i>

141
00:11:39,318 --> 00:11:41,654
Let it cook, will you?

142
00:11:42,863 --> 00:11:46,075
I can't wait that long.
One grill is plenty.

143
00:11:46,116 --> 00:11:48,327
Be honest, Mr. Kim.

144
00:11:48,369 --> 00:11:51,247
Was that really a pristine plot today?

145
00:11:51,288 --> 00:11:52,414
Hey, watch what you say.

146
00:11:53,249 --> 00:11:55,209
They're my regulars.

147
00:11:55,251 --> 00:12:00,506
It looked like it was facing
the North quite awkwardly,

148
00:12:00,548 --> 00:12:04,009
and the aura of the
site felt really quite off.

149
00:12:04,051 --> 00:12:06,470
Why don't you become a
geomancer yourself, now?

150
00:12:06,971 --> 00:12:10,099
If you think you know so well,
you should go on your own.

151
00:12:10,766 --> 00:12:12,434
So I've been doing some thinking.

152
00:12:12,476 --> 00:12:16,897
An average of 250,000 people
die every year in our country,

153
00:12:16,939 --> 00:12:18,691
and 30% of them get buried.

154
00:12:18,732 --> 00:12:22,319
Imagine how many people
have been buried in good plots

155
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:25,781
since the Joseon era
in this tiny country.

156
00:12:25,823 --> 00:12:29,577
So how can there still be so
many pristine plots around?

157
00:12:30,286 --> 00:12:32,413
- It just doesn't make sense...
- That plot...

158
00:12:33,539 --> 00:12:35,541
was a 65 out of 100.

159
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:37,501
Right, it wasn't a 100.

160
00:12:37,543 --> 00:12:40,087
They're drying up.
There aren't any more.

161
00:12:40,129 --> 00:12:45,384
Funeral directors like you
are hired by corporations,

162
00:12:45,426 --> 00:12:49,889
and men like me who sell plots just
poke around construction sites.

163
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:53,559
It's all over. We're the
last ones standing.

164
00:12:53,601 --> 00:12:54,894
Have a drink.

165
00:12:54,935 --> 00:12:56,937
Hold on, they're here already.

166
00:12:57,438 --> 00:12:59,064
You came so early.

167
00:12:59,106 --> 00:13:00,399
It's been a while.

168
00:13:00,441 --> 00:13:02,568
- Good evening.
- Hey, there.

169
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:06,405
Goodness, I could smell the pine
mushrooms all the way in Seoul.

170
00:13:06,447 --> 00:13:08,425
- I just had to bring myself.
- He ate all of them.

171
00:13:08,449 --> 00:13:09,783
What are you talking about?

172
00:13:10,451 --> 00:13:12,036
- Have you been well?
- Come on in.

173
00:13:12,077 --> 00:13:13,454
Sorry for not calling often.

174
00:13:13,496 --> 00:13:15,080
It can't be helped if you're busy.

175
00:13:15,122 --> 00:13:17,792
By the way, Bong-gil. Your
looks have gotten better.

176
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:18,793
You really think so?

177
00:13:18,834 --> 00:13:20,377
Don't even mention it.

178
00:13:20,419 --> 00:13:23,297
The ladies all want him around.
It's inflating his ego.

179
00:13:23,881 --> 00:13:26,425
How long has it been? Three years?

180
00:13:26,467 --> 00:13:28,928
Yes, time really flies.

181
00:13:28,969 --> 00:13:31,889
How's business lately?

182
00:13:31,931 --> 00:13:35,059
So-so, you know. It's off-season.

183
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,645
Which is why I brought...

184
00:13:37,686 --> 00:13:39,688
Wait a minute, I...

185
00:13:40,356 --> 00:13:42,733
Mr. Ko, do you smell that?

186
00:13:42,775 --> 00:13:45,319
What smell? Perhaps this?

187
00:13:45,361 --> 00:13:47,780
That's right, I smell dough.

188
00:13:47,822 --> 00:13:49,240
Jeez.

189
00:13:49,907 --> 00:13:51,575
I tried my best to hide it.

190
00:13:53,327 --> 00:13:54,327
You got me.

191
00:13:56,664 --> 00:13:58,916
- Spill it already. What is it?
- We got you just right.

192
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:00,543
You gentlemen clue in so quickly.

193
00:14:07,091 --> 00:14:12,221
<i>We visited a strange family in the US
upon a request from a doctor friend.</i>

194
00:14:12,263 --> 00:14:14,140
<i>The family of Mr. Park Ji-yong.</i>

195
00:14:14,181 --> 00:14:16,725
<i>The patriarch is a Korean national,</i>

196
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:19,186
but everyone else including
Mr. Park are American citizens.

197
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:22,523
- They're apparently...
- Filthy rich.

198
00:14:23,107 --> 00:14:24,233
That's a good start.

199
00:14:25,609 --> 00:14:29,029
All the firstborns are haunted,
including a newborn.

200
00:14:30,739 --> 00:14:32,158
They held out long enough.

201
00:14:33,284 --> 00:14:34,702
It isn't possession?

202
00:14:34,743 --> 00:14:36,996
It's not at that stage yet,

203
00:14:37,955 --> 00:14:42,001
but it's obviously the Grave's Calling.

204
00:14:44,670 --> 00:14:48,591
Are you really going to dig
up your grandfather's grave?

205
00:14:50,801 --> 00:14:52,761
It's been almost 100 years.

206
00:14:54,054 --> 00:14:55,431
I don't need your approval.

207
00:14:55,931 --> 00:14:57,349
I've made up my mind.

208
00:15:00,269 --> 00:15:02,480
You really believe in such things?

209
00:15:03,731 --> 00:15:07,359
And you think your aunt
in Korea will agree on this?

210
00:15:10,905 --> 00:15:12,364
I'm the head of the family,

211
00:15:13,699 --> 00:15:15,159
so I make the decisions.

212
00:15:17,495 --> 00:15:20,831
I don't trust those people.

213
00:15:21,624 --> 00:15:23,834
This could get out of hand.

214
00:15:24,418 --> 00:15:26,086
The baby will get better in time.

215
00:15:28,255 --> 00:15:32,551
Let's pray together
and seek treatments.

216
00:15:44,647 --> 00:15:49,693
We just have to live quietly
away from everything.

217
00:16:09,964 --> 00:16:13,259
Who cares if her belly's
full during the wedding?

218
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,052
It's the best gift you could ask for.

219
00:16:15,094 --> 00:16:18,931
But even so, a grandchild?
And one with blonde hair, no less.

220
00:16:18,973 --> 00:16:20,933
The baby will have blue eyes!

221
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,893
What an old fart.

222
00:16:22,935 --> 00:16:25,938
Will she be staying in
Germany after the wedding?

223
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:28,691
Of course not. She has
to come back to Korea.

224
00:16:29,358 --> 00:16:35,406
Anyway, I was worried about
the cost of her wedding.

225
00:16:35,447 --> 00:16:37,032
We caught a big game just in time.

226
00:16:37,074 --> 00:16:38,159
Indeed.

227
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:44,415
Our Lord sends us pension
just when the time is right.

228
00:16:44,457 --> 00:16:45,457
Amen.

229
00:16:47,251 --> 00:16:52,256
How rich do you think this man is to
pay us 500 million won to relocate?

230
00:16:52,923 --> 00:16:54,633
He probably paid more.

231
00:16:54,675 --> 00:16:56,010
What? More?

232
00:16:56,051 --> 00:16:59,638
You know how Hwa-rim can be.

233
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,307
You think she didn't take a cut?

234
00:17:01,348 --> 00:17:06,227
Right, she wouldn't
hesitate to exploit us.

235
00:17:11,192 --> 00:17:15,571
May I get your grandfather's
name and hometown first?

236
00:17:15,613 --> 00:17:21,452
I normally check the family's reputation
and occupations before the job,

237
00:17:21,494 --> 00:17:23,870
but since you're in a rush...

238
00:17:23,913 --> 00:17:28,334
Shouldn't you earn the
trust of the employer first?

239
00:17:33,714 --> 00:17:34,757
Trust?

240
00:17:36,050 --> 00:17:37,301
Very well.

241
00:17:37,343 --> 00:17:40,513
We can call this off
if you're not up for it.

242
00:17:40,554 --> 00:17:42,640
Can you promise me two things?

243
00:17:43,557 --> 00:17:46,101
From here on, keep
everything confidential.

244
00:17:46,769 --> 00:17:48,813
And cremate him right away.

245
00:17:50,689 --> 00:17:51,689
With the coffin.

246
00:17:53,484 --> 00:17:55,027
With the coffin?

247
00:17:55,069 --> 00:17:56,445
Don't bother opening it?

248
00:17:57,363 --> 00:17:58,697
Does it matter?

249
00:17:59,615 --> 00:18:03,202
I was told that it'd be either
relocation or cremation anyway.

250
00:18:03,244 --> 00:18:05,162
Under normal circumstances,

251
00:18:05,204 --> 00:18:08,249
we would first notify the town office,

252
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:12,253
open the coffin, and have the mortician
check the status of the bones.

253
00:18:12,294 --> 00:18:15,714
And then it would be
relocated or cremated.

254
00:18:15,756 --> 00:18:16,799
Okay?

255
00:18:22,221 --> 00:18:25,391
Let's go and check out the plot first.

256
00:18:25,432 --> 00:18:28,727
My parents and relatives
are against this adamantly.

257
00:18:28,769 --> 00:18:31,981
- I would like it to be done as swiftly...
- So let's check the plot first.

258
00:18:37,778 --> 00:18:40,114
Northern Gangwon...

259
00:18:40,156 --> 00:18:42,408
I've got a bad feeling about this.

260
00:18:42,449 --> 00:18:46,203
I find it weird that he doesn't
want the coffin opened.

261
00:18:46,745 --> 00:18:49,290
Shouldn't the bones be
checked regardless?

262
00:18:49,915 --> 00:18:51,375
He'll skip the shrouding then?

263
00:18:54,003 --> 00:18:56,589
Could there be something
inside the coffin?

264
00:18:57,089 --> 00:18:59,592
<i>Boguk Temple</i>

265
00:19:26,660 --> 00:19:28,100
<i>No Entry
This is a private property</i>

266
00:20:45,822 --> 00:20:48,158
Ever seen a grave at a mountain peak?

267
00:20:48,658 --> 00:20:49,784
It's rare.

268
00:20:51,161 --> 00:20:53,455
Do you know this mountain?

269
00:20:53,496 --> 00:20:54,914
No, never heard of it.

270
00:20:56,207 --> 00:20:59,085
You claim to know
every inch of this land.

271
00:20:59,127 --> 00:21:00,295
How could you not?

272
00:21:01,504 --> 00:21:03,590
I only seek pristine plots.

273
00:22:07,111 --> 00:22:09,155
What an incredible view.

274
00:22:09,197 --> 00:22:10,365
Very nice.

275
00:22:10,406 --> 00:22:13,660
You can even see North Korea
from here. You see that?

276
00:22:18,456 --> 00:22:20,576
The grave itself is quite
plain for such a grand plot.

277
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:54,659
Do you see something there?

278
00:22:57,078 --> 00:22:58,496
There's no name.

279
00:23:09,924 --> 00:23:14,304
Can you tell me who suggested this
plot for your grandfather's grave?

280
00:23:14,888 --> 00:23:18,766
A famous monk at the time
found the most auspicious plot

281
00:23:20,310 --> 00:23:22,437
because my grandfather made
a significant contribution

282
00:23:22,479 --> 00:23:23,938
- to the country.
- A monk?

283
00:23:24,522 --> 00:23:27,734
Yes, I heard they went by
the Buddhist name "Gisune."

284
00:23:27,775 --> 00:23:28,985
"Gisune"?

285
00:23:30,069 --> 00:23:31,404
That's a unique name.

286
00:23:32,572 --> 00:23:35,492
The grave feels quite plain
despite what you've said.

287
00:23:36,242 --> 00:23:38,328
I was told they decided
on a nondescript one

288
00:23:38,369 --> 00:23:40,663
because of rampant grave
robberies at the time.

289
00:23:51,174 --> 00:23:52,175
What do you think?

290
00:23:53,218 --> 00:23:54,677
I'll settle on a date then.

291
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:59,390
What is it? Is something off?

292
00:24:05,188 --> 00:24:06,439
Mr. Park.

293
00:24:07,148 --> 00:24:10,360
I don't think I can take this job.

294
00:24:13,988 --> 00:24:15,615
He's screwing us again.

295
00:24:15,657 --> 00:24:16,657
Mr. Kim!

296
00:24:17,867 --> 00:24:19,619
- What is up with him?
- What is it?

297
00:24:20,078 --> 00:24:21,412
Is it that bad?

298
00:24:22,705 --> 00:24:24,374
Is there no way?

299
00:24:26,417 --> 00:24:28,044
Why won't you tell us?

300
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:35,301
It's got a great view and
everything. What's the matter?

301
00:24:36,636 --> 00:24:39,139
You know how much this job pays.

302
00:24:40,014 --> 00:24:42,225
Come on, what's going on?

303
00:24:45,478 --> 00:24:47,564
I'm sure you all understand

304
00:24:47,605 --> 00:24:49,941
what happens if we mess
with the wrong grave.

305
00:24:50,608 --> 00:24:53,236
I've been selling plots
for 40 years now,

306
00:24:53,278 --> 00:24:55,572
but this one is a plot
I've never heard of.

307
00:24:55,613 --> 00:24:56,698
It's vile.

308
00:24:57,866 --> 00:25:02,162
No human should ever be
buried in a place like this.

309
00:25:02,203 --> 00:25:09,002
Dealing with something like that
could get everyone involved killed.

310
00:25:09,043 --> 00:25:10,462
Do you understand?

311
00:25:10,503 --> 00:25:12,338
Hwa-rim, you saw the foxes, no?

312
00:25:14,924 --> 00:25:18,303
Foxes at a gravesite
is an ominous sign.

313
00:25:20,763 --> 00:25:22,682
It's the vilest plot.

314
00:25:33,109 --> 00:25:36,237
That's the last time
I saw my son smile.

315
00:25:37,822 --> 00:25:40,533
We conceived twice before him,

316
00:25:40,575 --> 00:25:42,869
but they were miscarried
for unknown reasons.

317
00:25:42,911 --> 00:25:44,704
We managed to give
birth to him at our age.

318
00:25:46,748 --> 00:25:49,250
Do you have any children, Mr. Kim?

319
00:25:49,292 --> 00:25:51,252
Yes, I do.

320
00:25:51,294 --> 00:25:53,797
I have a daughter who's
getting married soon.

321
00:25:54,631 --> 00:25:56,382
Congratulations.

322
00:25:56,424 --> 00:25:58,009
Don't even mention it.

323
00:25:58,051 --> 00:26:00,386
Is your daughter in
the same line of work?

324
00:26:00,428 --> 00:26:05,642
She majored in Aerospace Engineering
and works for an airline in Germany.

325
00:26:06,643 --> 00:26:09,145
She's in a frenzy
preparing for her wedding.

326
00:26:10,063 --> 00:26:11,147
Very interesting.

327
00:26:11,773 --> 00:26:15,318
A geomancer father and an
aerospace engineer daughter.

328
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:19,656
The thing is, if you look
at both fields side-by-side,

329
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:22,617
they have quite a lot of similarities.

330
00:26:23,618 --> 00:26:26,496
Yin-yang and the five
elements are about studying

331
00:26:26,538 --> 00:26:29,749
water, fire, metal, and
wood with earth as the basis.

332
00:26:29,791 --> 00:26:32,752
It's about analyzing nature
under these conditions,

333
00:26:32,794 --> 00:26:35,088
- and aerospace is about...
- Then...

334
00:26:37,715 --> 00:26:39,384
can't you save my child?

335
00:26:45,056 --> 00:26:46,975
You're hiding something
from us, Mr. Park.

336
00:26:50,478 --> 00:26:51,396
What do you...

337
00:26:51,437 --> 00:26:55,191
38.3417, 128.3189.

338
00:26:55,817 --> 00:26:57,652
A longitude and a latitude.

339
00:26:57,694 --> 00:27:00,363
They were engraved
behind the gravestone.

340
00:27:00,405 --> 00:27:05,451
I don't know who this Gisune was,

341
00:27:05,493 --> 00:27:09,497
but it's absolutely clear that
they had some kind of intention.

342
00:27:15,587 --> 00:27:18,715
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

343
00:27:20,175 --> 00:27:21,843
And I'm not hiding
anything from you two.

344
00:27:22,802 --> 00:27:24,387
Let me make it clear.

345
00:27:24,429 --> 00:27:27,432
Relocating a grave from
an unknown plot like that

346
00:27:27,474 --> 00:27:28,808
is extremely dangerous.

347
00:27:29,392 --> 00:27:31,394
It's like digging for a
mine with bare hands.

348
00:27:31,436 --> 00:27:33,396
We could try a withdrawal ritual.

349
00:27:36,274 --> 00:27:37,609
I knew you'd say that.

350
00:27:40,361 --> 00:27:42,780
We can do it while relocating.

351
00:27:43,865 --> 00:27:46,159
You already know the solution.

352
00:27:46,826 --> 00:27:49,287
I don't trust anything
that I haven't done before.

353
00:27:49,329 --> 00:27:53,833
The combination will be a first,
but it's not theoretically impossible.

354
00:27:54,709 --> 00:27:55,794
Wait.

355
00:27:57,128 --> 00:28:01,174
Why are we waiting for your permission?

356
00:28:01,216 --> 00:28:03,259
You're not the only
geomancer in the country.

357
00:28:04,093 --> 00:28:06,262
This is why it's tough
working with old geezers.

358
00:28:06,304 --> 00:28:09,516
- Watch it.
- The child is in pain.

359
00:28:17,982 --> 00:28:20,235
This hotel is on a good plot.

360
00:28:23,571 --> 00:28:26,991
<i>The Passing of Misfortune
is a type of deception ritual.</i>

361
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:30,203
<i>We'll get five diggers
with the pig zodiac sign</i>

362
00:28:30,245 --> 00:28:32,831
<i>and five sacrificial
pigs tied together,</i>

363
00:28:32,872 --> 00:28:35,083
<i>and we'll have the men dig the grave.</i>

364
00:28:35,792 --> 00:28:39,003
<i>The vile energy from the ground
will then be transferred to the pigs,</i>

365
00:28:39,045 --> 00:28:40,713
<i>which I'll whisk away.</i>

366
00:28:43,299 --> 00:28:44,551
Your aunt is here.

367
00:28:45,135 --> 00:28:47,720
Seems like your mother
shared what's happening.

368
00:30:45,130 --> 00:30:48,883
Let's go!

369
00:30:53,805 --> 00:30:57,976
Let's go!

370
00:30:58,893 --> 00:31:01,104
Here we go!

371
00:31:11,739 --> 00:31:14,701
Let's go!

372
00:31:34,387 --> 00:31:35,763
All right!

373
00:31:37,807 --> 00:31:39,601
Go for it!

374
00:31:42,645 --> 00:31:48,026
- Appease the guardian!
- Appease the guardian!

375
00:31:52,739 --> 00:31:55,742
Exhumation!

376
00:31:56,659 --> 00:31:57,994
Exhumation!

377
00:32:01,748 --> 00:32:03,541
Appease the guardian!

378
00:32:03,583 --> 00:32:06,044
Mountain guardian!

379
00:32:11,090 --> 00:32:13,426
Appease the guardian!

380
00:33:45,934 --> 00:33:47,227
There it is.

381
00:33:56,403 --> 00:33:57,821
Reveal!

382
00:33:57,863 --> 00:33:59,573
- Reveal!
- Reveal!

383
00:34:13,003 --> 00:34:14,671
The chill is immense.

384
00:34:31,271 --> 00:34:33,689
It's too old to make anything out.

385
00:34:50,249 --> 00:34:51,667
What's this?

386
00:34:52,876 --> 00:34:54,503
It's a coffin made of juniper tree.

387
00:34:54,544 --> 00:34:57,171
Only the royal families used this.

388
00:34:57,214 --> 00:34:59,383
I can't believe I'm seeing this here.

389
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:04,179
- Coffin removal!
- Coffin removal!

390
00:35:07,182 --> 00:35:09,685
Good, now let's move slowly.

391
00:35:09,726 --> 00:35:12,146
- Lower the head!
- Take it easy.

392
00:35:12,187 --> 00:35:13,147
Careful now.

393
00:35:13,188 --> 00:35:15,566
Load the coffin
straight into the hearse.

394
00:35:15,607 --> 00:35:17,276
We're heading to the crematorium,

395
00:35:17,317 --> 00:35:20,070
so bury the tombstone and
make sure to tidy up afterward.

396
00:35:21,738 --> 00:35:22,948
Let's swap ropes.

397
00:35:22,990 --> 00:35:25,200
- And remember not to eat meat today.
- Okay.

398
00:35:31,707 --> 00:35:33,459
Thank you for everything.

399
00:35:42,759 --> 00:35:43,759
Yes?

400
00:35:44,511 --> 00:35:47,389
A soul that hasn't even been
shrouded is riding with you.

401
00:35:47,431 --> 00:35:48,671
Let's be respectful, all right?

402
00:35:51,310 --> 00:35:52,186
Come on.

403
00:35:52,227 --> 00:35:54,813
I'm Ko Young-geun, the man
who shrouded the late president.

404
00:35:54,855 --> 00:35:57,107
The job is done, so loosen up.

405
00:36:13,123 --> 00:36:14,123
Let's see.

406
00:36:15,834 --> 00:36:17,044
There's nothing there.

407
00:36:17,085 --> 00:36:18,086
Let's go.

408
00:36:28,055 --> 00:36:29,306
What is that?

409
00:36:29,348 --> 00:36:30,432
Damn it.

410
00:37:16,854 --> 00:37:19,064
What in the world?

411
00:37:40,961 --> 00:37:41,879
Mr. Park.

412
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:44,089
We'll have to delay the cremation

413
00:37:44,131 --> 00:37:46,216
because of the unexpected rainfall.

414
00:37:48,010 --> 00:37:49,178
Why is that?

415
00:37:49,219 --> 00:37:51,138
It's not like it's done outdoors.

416
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:54,349
When cremation takes
place on a rainy day,

417
00:37:55,100 --> 00:37:57,728
the soul cannot reach a good afterlife.

418
00:37:58,312 --> 00:38:00,439
It may sound superstitious to you,

419
00:38:00,939 --> 00:38:03,379
but I'm letting you know for
professional and ethical reasons.

420
00:38:05,486 --> 00:38:07,571
This happens from time to time.

421
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:12,701
We can hold the body in
a nearby hospital morgue

422
00:38:12,743 --> 00:38:15,412
and reschedule the cremation
when the weather improves.

423
00:38:16,330 --> 00:38:19,708
Wouldn't we have to submit a
funeral report if we go to a hospital?

424
00:38:19,750 --> 00:38:20,959
Mr. Kim!

425
00:38:21,001 --> 00:38:23,337
I got confirmation!

426
00:38:23,378 --> 00:38:24,713
We're good to go!

427
00:38:24,755 --> 00:38:28,217
Don't worry about that.
We know these people.

428
00:38:32,054 --> 00:38:34,890
Why the entire coffin
even after relocation?

429
00:38:34,932 --> 00:38:37,392
The head mourner won't let us open it.

430
00:38:37,434 --> 00:38:38,519
Here.

431
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:40,479
Come on, there's no need.

432
00:38:41,021 --> 00:38:44,566
Don't be that way, take it.

433
00:38:44,608 --> 00:38:46,443
Jeez.

434
00:38:47,444 --> 00:38:50,405
Well, the last group of the day
did just leave, so it's quiet inside.

435
00:38:50,447 --> 00:38:51,615
That's good.

436
00:38:52,115 --> 00:38:54,743
But having it pour on cremation day,

437
00:38:54,785 --> 00:38:57,246
he's got a long trip to the afterlife.

438
00:39:06,213 --> 00:39:08,590
They're rescheduling the cremation?

439
00:39:08,632 --> 00:39:09,883
Yes.

440
00:39:10,717 --> 00:39:13,220
Are you sure you can
trust those people?

441
00:39:13,262 --> 00:39:15,889
I paid them enough and spoke
to them on a need-to-know basis.

442
00:39:16,807 --> 00:39:18,600
You don't need to worry.

443
00:39:19,309 --> 00:39:21,019
Since we've gained some time,

444
00:39:22,271 --> 00:39:25,607
let's consider moving him
to our family gravesite.

445
00:39:27,151 --> 00:39:29,736
I'm still against the cremation.

446
00:39:30,737 --> 00:39:33,448
He was my father, so
I get the say in this.

447
00:39:35,742 --> 00:39:36,994
Go and get some rest.

448
00:39:42,624 --> 00:39:46,879
Let's just leave it here
since we can't open it.

449
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:49,798
I'll take care of the humidity level.

450
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:50,883
Thanks again.

451
00:39:52,551 --> 00:39:54,136
Just look at that coffin.

452
00:39:54,761 --> 00:39:56,722
He must've earned some royal favors.

453
00:39:57,931 --> 00:39:59,349
Good to see you.

454
00:40:01,685 --> 00:40:04,062
The head mourner and his
family all headed back to Seoul.

455
00:40:05,022 --> 00:40:07,816
But Hwa-rim told me
that she'll join us here.

456
00:40:09,401 --> 00:40:10,777
It's a chilly day.

457
00:40:10,819 --> 00:40:13,155
Go and have some hot soup.

458
00:40:14,490 --> 00:40:15,866
I need to step out for a bit.

459
00:40:16,825 --> 00:40:17,825
All right.

460
00:40:37,513 --> 00:40:40,808
<i>Boguk Temple</i>

461
00:41:12,297 --> 00:41:14,007
I don't think I've seen you before.

462
00:41:14,049 --> 00:41:15,049
Can I help you?

463
00:41:15,551 --> 00:41:16,927
Pardon me for intruding.

464
00:41:17,594 --> 00:41:21,598
I saw a sign on the
road while driving by.

465
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:23,350
Is that so?

466
00:41:23,976 --> 00:41:28,814
It's just that I noticed the
geomancy symbol on it.

467
00:41:28,856 --> 00:41:30,607
I wanted to ask about it.

468
00:41:32,860 --> 00:41:34,111
Are you a geomancer?

469
00:41:34,153 --> 00:41:38,490
Yes, I was a protégé of Master Choi,

470
00:41:39,116 --> 00:41:42,995
and I'm barely making ends
meet by selling plots on my own.

471
00:41:43,036 --> 00:41:47,833
This place may look shabby now,
but it has existed for over 100 years.

472
00:41:48,542 --> 00:41:51,962
The head monk who
established this temple

473
00:41:52,004 --> 00:41:56,049
was renowned for his
geomancy expertise.

474
00:41:56,091 --> 00:41:57,092
I see.

475
00:41:57,759 --> 00:42:00,846
I can tell just by looking
at the site it's on.

476
00:42:00,888 --> 00:42:02,264
Speaking of which,

477
00:42:02,306 --> 00:42:07,060
was the head monk's name
Gisune by any chance?

478
00:42:08,061 --> 00:42:09,104
Gisune?

479
00:42:09,730 --> 00:42:11,815
No, he was called Wonbong.

480
00:42:12,483 --> 00:42:15,027
May I ask why you're inquiring?

481
00:42:15,068 --> 00:42:17,070
Oh, well...

482
00:42:17,112 --> 00:42:22,326
There's a nameless grave
at the peak of that mountain.

483
00:42:22,367 --> 00:42:24,161
Do you happen to know
anything about it?

484
00:42:24,203 --> 00:42:25,329
Of course.

485
00:42:25,954 --> 00:42:27,873
I'm not sure if it's still there,

486
00:42:28,540 --> 00:42:32,169
but I heard a lot of rumors
about it back in the day.

487
00:42:34,087 --> 00:42:35,839
What kind of rumors?

488
00:42:36,548 --> 00:42:38,300
Don't stay alone in this eerie place,

489
00:42:38,342 --> 00:42:40,803
and go have some hot
soup across the street.

490
00:42:40,844 --> 00:42:42,846
Sure, don't worry.

491
00:42:42,888 --> 00:42:44,306
- I'm off.
- Take care.

492
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:50,437
Why does everyone care
so much about my dinner?

493
00:42:58,654 --> 00:43:02,533
<i>There were rumors of
treasures buried in the grave.</i>

494
00:43:03,450 --> 00:43:04,451
<i>Treasures?</i>

495
00:43:06,411 --> 00:43:10,165
People would say it was the grave
of the richest man in Joseon

496
00:43:10,207 --> 00:43:12,709
or that of an unknown king.

497
00:43:13,293 --> 00:43:17,089
So there were quite a lot of grave
robbers flocking to this area.

498
00:43:18,382 --> 00:43:19,758
Grave robbers?

499
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:22,344
Some of them were arrested,

500
00:43:22,386 --> 00:43:25,514
while others crossed the
border to North Korea.

501
00:43:25,556 --> 00:43:27,891
So they never got to rob the grave?

502
00:43:27,933 --> 00:43:29,810
Probably never got a chance to.

503
00:43:29,852 --> 00:43:32,479
I heard it belonged to
a high-ranking official,

504
00:43:32,521 --> 00:43:34,189
so it was hard to even approach it.

505
00:43:36,024 --> 00:43:39,653
These were the tools they left behind.

506
00:43:47,327 --> 00:43:50,622
Can I ask why you're
asking about the grave?

507
00:43:55,419 --> 00:43:56,419
Because I...

508
00:43:57,171 --> 00:43:58,714
dug it up today.

509
00:44:06,430 --> 00:44:09,808
So? Were there treasures inside?

510
00:44:26,325 --> 00:44:28,285
Excuse me? What are you doing?

511
00:44:29,453 --> 00:44:30,453
Hey!

512
00:44:36,543 --> 00:44:38,170
Hwa-rim.

513
00:44:38,712 --> 00:44:39,712
Hey, you!

514
00:44:40,255 --> 00:44:42,299
Hwa-rim, are you okay?

515
00:44:46,470 --> 00:44:47,596
What?

516
00:44:47,638 --> 00:44:50,015
What do you mean, the
coffin's been opened?

517
00:44:51,391 --> 00:44:53,519
Damn those sticky fingers of his.

518
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:55,562
I paid him enough to leave it alone.

519
00:44:55,604 --> 00:44:56,939
I knew he felt off.

520
00:44:59,650 --> 00:45:01,485
Hey, what happened?

521
00:45:03,403 --> 00:45:04,738
Something flew past her.

522
00:45:06,573 --> 00:45:07,616
What did?

523
00:45:17,793 --> 00:45:19,378
Something came out of it.

524
00:45:20,462 --> 00:45:21,630
Something very vicious.

525
00:46:00,961 --> 00:46:03,255
Father...

526
00:46:05,507 --> 00:46:09,303
My father.

527
00:46:13,598 --> 00:46:15,266
<i>Jong-soon.</i>

528
00:46:16,517 --> 00:46:18,352
<i>My son.</i>

529
00:46:20,396 --> 00:46:22,523
<i>Open the window.</i>

530
00:46:24,025 --> 00:46:26,277
Father...

531
00:46:28,821 --> 00:46:31,782
Come inside.

532
00:47:00,311 --> 00:47:02,021
Father?

533
00:47:38,474 --> 00:47:43,688
<i>My loyal little boy...</i>

534
00:47:45,898 --> 00:47:50,027
<i>This is a land flowing
with milk and honey.</i>

535
00:47:52,071 --> 00:47:57,243
<i>Your father is cold and hungry.</i>

536
00:47:58,202 --> 00:48:00,121
I'm sorry.

537
00:49:04,185 --> 00:49:07,188
<i>The spirit has got to be
flying wild everywhere.</i>

538
00:49:07,230 --> 00:49:08,981
<i>The head mourner is in danger.</i>

539
00:49:09,023 --> 00:49:12,443
<i>You leave for Seoul
immediately, Mr. Kim.</i>

540
00:49:12,485 --> 00:49:15,613
<i>Meanwhile, we'll try to
summon the spirit back here.</i>

541
00:49:15,655 --> 00:49:18,324
You'll summon it from here?

542
00:49:18,366 --> 00:49:22,537
It screamed to be let out for a century,
only to have nobody free itself.

543
00:49:23,412 --> 00:49:25,081
Only resentment remains in the spirit.

544
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:29,252
He'll pay a visit to every
one of his descendants.

545
00:49:36,759 --> 00:49:38,845
What a mess we're in.

546
00:49:38,886 --> 00:49:41,323
It's pouring out, the coffin's open,
and a ghost's on the loose...

547
00:49:41,347 --> 00:49:43,224
I really didn't want to do this.

548
00:49:43,266 --> 00:49:45,143
Tell me about it.

549
00:49:48,521 --> 00:49:51,399
Will you two be okay
doing two rituals in a day?

550
00:49:52,024 --> 00:49:53,651
We'll be fine.

551
00:49:54,902 --> 00:49:57,071
Mr. Ko, make sure
to get the timing right.

552
00:49:57,113 --> 00:49:59,240
- Hold the rope tight when it enters.
- Right.

553
00:50:52,543 --> 00:50:53,628
Come forth.

554
00:51:38,965 --> 00:51:41,175
Here he comes.

555
00:51:52,478 --> 00:51:54,230
Come forth.

556
00:51:58,568 --> 00:51:59,861
He's here.

557
00:51:59,902 --> 00:52:02,196
Bong-gil!

558
00:52:02,238 --> 00:52:03,238
Hold tight!

559
00:52:39,525 --> 00:52:40,526
Hey, old man.

560
00:52:41,986 --> 00:52:43,321
Who are you?

561
00:52:44,572 --> 00:52:45,572
Huh?

562
00:52:47,116 --> 00:52:48,116
Bong-gil, hang onto him!

563
00:52:51,078 --> 00:52:54,832
What got you so riled up?

564
00:52:55,458 --> 00:52:57,627
Talk to me.

565
00:52:58,336 --> 00:53:00,505
Let it all out tonight.

566
00:53:01,631 --> 00:53:03,758
Don't go off elsewhere.

567
00:53:05,384 --> 00:53:06,969
I'm taking...

568
00:53:08,221 --> 00:53:09,931
my children with me.

569
00:53:13,059 --> 00:53:14,310
I can't allow that.

570
00:53:42,380 --> 00:53:43,589
We lost him.

571
00:53:44,257 --> 00:53:45,800
What do we do?

572
00:53:53,141 --> 00:53:54,475
Hello?

573
00:53:54,517 --> 00:53:57,603
<i>Mr. Park, this is Kim Sang-duk.
Is everything okay?</i>

574
00:53:58,729 --> 00:54:01,482
Yes, what's going on?

575
00:54:01,524 --> 00:54:02,775
<i>Thank goodness.</i>

576
00:54:03,276 --> 00:54:05,486
<i>It's just that there's been a mishap,</i>

577
00:54:05,528 --> 00:54:07,947
<i>so I'm on my way to you right now.</i>

578
00:54:07,989 --> 00:54:10,199
<i>I know it's late, but could
we talk when I arrive?</i>

579
00:54:10,241 --> 00:54:11,241
What?

580
00:54:12,160 --> 00:54:13,160
What's going on?

581
00:54:14,370 --> 00:54:17,665
<i>You're still at the same hotel, right?</i>

582
00:54:17,707 --> 00:54:20,710
<i>I'm almost there. I'll be right up.</i>

583
00:54:21,294 --> 00:54:22,294
One moment.

584
00:54:22,962 --> 00:54:24,172
Who is it?

585
00:54:24,213 --> 00:54:26,382
It's me, Kim Sang-duk.

586
00:54:26,424 --> 00:54:30,428
<i>Hello? What's going on?</i>

587
00:54:31,137 --> 00:54:33,431
Mr. Kim, are you outside my room?

588
00:54:33,473 --> 00:54:34,765
Excuse me, Mr. Park?

589
00:54:34,807 --> 00:54:37,185
<i>No, no!</i>

590
00:54:37,226 --> 00:54:38,436
<i>That's not me.</i>

591
00:54:38,478 --> 00:54:40,813
<i>Your grandfather's
coffin has been opened.</i>

592
00:54:41,355 --> 00:54:43,900
- What?
- Please open the door!

593
00:54:43,941 --> 00:54:44,942
My grandfather's coffin?

594
00:54:44,984 --> 00:54:47,737
<i>My apologies, but it was unsealed.</i>

595
00:54:47,778 --> 00:54:49,322
Is something going on inside?

596
00:54:49,363 --> 00:54:52,783
<i>Don't ever open the
door, and just stay put.</i>

597
00:54:52,825 --> 00:54:54,577
<i>- I'm heading your way.</i>
- Mr. Park!

598
00:54:55,161 --> 00:54:59,373
<i>Only listen to me and act calmly.</i>

599
00:54:59,415 --> 00:55:01,125
<i>Listen carefully, Mr. Park.</i>

600
00:55:01,167 --> 00:55:04,045
<i>Walk away from the door
and get to the window.</i>

601
00:55:06,923 --> 00:55:08,132
Please open the door!

602
00:55:08,841 --> 00:55:11,511
It's an urgent matter I
have to explain to you!

603
00:55:11,552 --> 00:55:13,471
<i>Don't answer, and don't listen.</i>

604
00:55:14,013 --> 00:55:16,557
<i>Go to the window and open it.</i>

605
00:55:16,599 --> 00:55:19,519
<i>Your grandfather will protect
you, so you must let him in.</i>

606
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:20,812
Mr. Park!

607
00:55:21,604 --> 00:55:23,272
<i>Just listen to me and hurry!</i>

608
00:55:27,401 --> 00:55:28,401
<i>I said, open the window!</i>

609
00:56:09,861 --> 00:56:10,861
Mr. Park!

610
00:56:16,284 --> 00:56:17,285
Mr. Park?

611
00:56:23,416 --> 00:56:24,416
Are you okay?

612
00:56:31,382 --> 00:56:33,968
Proud young men of the peninsula.

613
00:56:34,927 --> 00:56:38,639
Do you hear the sound of hundreds
of airplanes and artillery?

614
00:56:39,515 --> 00:56:41,851
Push forward, sons of the Empire!

615
00:56:43,060 --> 00:56:47,064
Raise your bayonets
under the Rising Sun flag!

616
00:56:48,149 --> 00:56:51,068
Serve your devotion
to the Japanese Empire

617
00:56:51,110 --> 00:56:54,822
for the unification
of Greater East Asia!

618
00:57:07,293 --> 00:57:08,293
Ambulance...

619
00:57:08,628 --> 00:57:09,628
Call an ambulance.

620
00:57:10,797 --> 00:57:13,257
Please call an ambulance.

621
00:57:14,133 --> 00:57:15,259
Call a damn ambulance!

622
00:57:21,516 --> 00:57:23,976
I'm telling you, I saw it
with my own two eyes.

623
00:57:24,018 --> 00:57:26,062
This could lead to
a series of funerals!

624
00:57:26,103 --> 00:57:28,248
- We're going to the crematorium.
- All right, get going.

625
00:57:28,272 --> 00:57:31,692
You get their permission to cremate,
and we'll stand by from there.

626
00:57:51,504 --> 00:57:54,215
Your grandfather's coffin is...

627
00:57:54,257 --> 00:57:56,134
The fox severed the tiger's waist.

628
00:57:58,136 --> 00:57:59,262
Pardon me?

629
00:58:05,852 --> 00:58:08,604
The fox severed the tiger's waist.

630
00:58:22,160 --> 00:58:24,745
I said the fox severed
the tiger's waist.

631
00:58:52,273 --> 00:58:55,485
Mother, is everything okay?

632
00:58:56,736 --> 00:58:58,863
She must be tired from the trip.

633
00:59:00,573 --> 00:59:02,033
I need to get some rest.

634
00:59:08,538 --> 00:59:10,832
Joseph's condition
seems to be better today.

635
00:59:10,874 --> 00:59:12,000
Doesn't it?

636
00:59:12,042 --> 00:59:13,835
Anyways, I cannot reach anyone at home.

637
00:59:13,877 --> 00:59:15,337
So I'll go back home and check.

638
00:59:15,921 --> 00:59:17,255
Sure. I'll be here.

639
00:59:23,804 --> 00:59:25,722
It's because this is an urgent matter!

640
00:59:25,764 --> 00:59:27,200
Have I ever asked
for a favor like this?

641
00:59:27,224 --> 00:59:28,600
<i>It's too late in the night.</i>

642
00:59:28,642 --> 00:59:30,852
We'll be there soon. Please hurry!

643
00:59:30,894 --> 00:59:33,396
<i>Cremating in this weather is nonsense.</i>

644
00:59:33,438 --> 00:59:34,481
<i>What did the mourner say?</i>

645
00:59:34,523 --> 00:59:36,483
I told you, something
came out of the coffin!

646
00:59:37,067 --> 00:59:38,276
You must know what that means.

647
00:59:39,152 --> 00:59:40,792
The body needs to be
cremated immediately.

648
00:59:41,404 --> 00:59:43,365
Please call his family in the US.

649
00:59:43,406 --> 00:59:45,700
Pardon? What do you mean?

650
00:59:45,742 --> 00:59:47,285
You saw what happened.

651
00:59:47,327 --> 00:59:49,329
The baby is next.

652
01:00:16,606 --> 01:00:18,733
No one in the US is answering.

653
01:00:21,236 --> 01:00:22,236
Then...

654
01:00:42,007 --> 01:00:43,008
What's this?

655
01:00:43,049 --> 01:00:45,009
You exhumed the coffin
but didn't shroud the body?

656
01:00:45,510 --> 01:00:47,012
You'll cremate the entire coffin?

657
01:00:48,263 --> 01:00:50,724
Things will get messy if
the town office finds out.

658
01:00:56,229 --> 01:00:57,772
<i>My father's coffin?</i>

659
01:00:57,814 --> 01:00:59,816
I don't quite understand it myself.

660
01:00:59,858 --> 01:01:02,152
But he said it has to be
cremated immediately.

661
01:01:02,736 --> 01:01:04,738
What do you mean?

662
01:01:04,779 --> 01:01:07,449
Ma'am, we must hurry.

663
01:01:07,491 --> 01:01:11,244
Your father's spirit is headed
to the baby in the US.

664
01:01:33,558 --> 01:01:35,143
- I'll fire it up.
- One second.

665
01:01:35,185 --> 01:01:37,354
The mourner hasn't given us the go yet.

666
01:01:37,395 --> 01:01:39,272
<i>We're unable to reach
your family in the US.</i>

667
01:01:39,314 --> 01:01:42,526
<i>Only you can give us the permission
to cremate the coffin.</i>

668
01:02:03,505 --> 01:02:06,424
Is this really the only way?

669
01:02:24,276 --> 01:02:25,277
Very well.

670
01:02:26,236 --> 01:02:27,445
<i>Please proceed.</i>

671
01:02:27,487 --> 01:02:28,487
Yes, ma'am.

672
01:02:31,032 --> 01:02:32,032
<i>Burn it.</i>

673
01:02:55,223 --> 01:02:56,933
What a terrible fate.

674
01:02:57,517 --> 01:02:59,144
Too bad he won't
reach a good afterlife.

675
01:03:47,567 --> 01:03:53,240
<i>Off on a journey</i>

676
01:03:54,032 --> 01:03:59,913
<i>Off on a journey</i>

677
01:04:01,540 --> 01:04:06,711
<i>Beach rose of Myeongsasimni</i>

678
01:04:07,546 --> 01:04:12,551
<i>Flowers bloom, leaves fall
Do not be saddened</i>

679
01:04:25,230 --> 01:04:30,318
<i>Which saint led your bier?</i>

680
01:04:30,360 --> 01:04:34,948
<i>- Why has the grim reaper appeared?
- Why has the grim reaper appeared?</i>

681
01:04:47,377 --> 01:04:49,796
<i>Re-routing to your destination.</i>

682
01:04:55,844 --> 01:04:57,262
<i>Remember Chang-min, Mr. Kim?</i>

683
01:04:57,971 --> 01:05:01,683
<i>He said he's fallen sick
after the exhumation.</i>

684
01:05:01,725 --> 01:05:04,644
<i>Would you mind giving him a
visit when things cool down?</i>

685
01:05:04,686 --> 01:05:06,771
<i>Make a left turn.</i>

686
01:05:07,355 --> 01:05:09,107
<i>The hospital is clueless.</i>

687
01:05:09,149 --> 01:05:11,401
<i>I just wasted money
on a bunch of tests.</i>

688
01:05:13,195 --> 01:05:17,365
<i>I have nightmares and hallucinations.</i>

689
01:05:18,825 --> 01:05:19,825
Mr. Kim...

690
01:05:22,454 --> 01:05:24,831
I think I'm getting
punished by the gods.

691
01:05:26,750 --> 01:05:30,170
<i>I saw something while cleaning
up after the exhumation that day.</i>

692
01:05:31,505 --> 01:05:32,798
It looked so strange.

693
01:05:34,132 --> 01:05:35,425
It was a snake...

694
01:05:36,176 --> 01:05:37,427
What? A snake?

695
01:05:38,678 --> 01:05:40,722
Damn it, I should've just let it be.

696
01:05:42,140 --> 01:05:44,810
Please do me a favor, Mr. Kim.

697
01:05:45,477 --> 01:05:49,231
Find the snake I cut in half
and say a prayer to it, will you?

698
01:05:53,527 --> 01:05:55,946
<i>I really didn't want
to go there that day.</i>

699
01:05:55,987 --> 01:05:57,405
<i>I really didn't want to.</i>

700
01:05:58,114 --> 01:06:01,368
<i>That place felt weird
to begin with, didn't it?</i>

701
01:06:02,536 --> 01:06:04,287
<i>Why was a grave
there in the first place?</i>

702
01:07:50,101 --> 01:07:51,144
Double interment.

703
01:07:52,062 --> 01:07:53,605
Yes, I'm busy.

704
01:07:54,147 --> 01:07:56,107
I'm doing a Bible study
with church friends.

705
01:07:56,149 --> 01:07:57,734
Here's 50,000 won for you.

706
01:07:58,360 --> 01:07:59,360
Go.

707
01:07:59,694 --> 01:08:00,737
What?

708
01:08:03,323 --> 01:08:04,366
A double interment?

709
01:08:04,407 --> 01:08:06,076
Yes, just under the coffin.

710
01:08:07,077 --> 01:08:08,328
By the way, Mr. Ko,

711
01:08:08,954 --> 01:08:11,414
have you ever seen a
coffin buried vertically?

712
01:08:15,585 --> 01:08:16,586
Yes?

713
01:08:18,755 --> 01:08:19,840
Hwa-rim?

714
01:08:20,882 --> 01:08:21,925
Here we go.

715
01:08:22,884 --> 01:08:24,135
In two beats.

716
01:08:38,108 --> 01:08:42,112
Coffins could go vertical
when the ground shifts...

717
01:08:43,905 --> 01:08:45,447
but still, this is too big.

718
01:08:47,032 --> 01:08:48,285
What the hell is this?

719
01:08:54,249 --> 01:08:55,876
What's that about?

720
01:09:04,675 --> 01:09:05,885
I think this chain...

721
01:09:07,179 --> 01:09:09,347
is to prevent someone from opening it.

722
01:09:11,016 --> 01:09:12,767
- Or...
- Or what?

723
01:09:13,434 --> 01:09:14,603
Or the opposite.

724
01:09:18,063 --> 01:09:19,691
Let's pull it out and examine it.

725
01:09:19,733 --> 01:09:21,358
For what?

726
01:09:21,401 --> 01:09:23,737
We should contact the mourners first.

727
01:09:23,778 --> 01:09:25,530
We've got the payment
left to discuss too.

728
01:09:25,572 --> 01:09:28,700
Let's not mess with this.

729
01:09:33,871 --> 01:09:34,956
Let's pull it out first.

730
01:09:35,624 --> 01:09:37,626
I'm sure it belongs to the family.

731
01:09:37,666 --> 01:09:40,086
We can't just leave it like this.

732
01:09:41,545 --> 01:09:43,130
But how do we...

733
01:09:43,799 --> 01:09:45,467
Let's pull it out. Go get a rope.

734
01:09:45,509 --> 01:09:46,675
Hurry, the sun's setting.

735
01:09:50,679 --> 01:09:52,557
Pull hard on the count of three.

736
01:09:53,266 --> 01:09:55,184
One, two, three!

737
01:10:10,951 --> 01:10:12,410
How is that for a human?

738
01:11:01,877 --> 01:11:03,670
Where is he going?

739
01:11:09,801 --> 01:11:10,801
<i>Boguk Temple</i>

740
01:11:23,315 --> 01:11:24,483
What's going on?

741
01:11:24,524 --> 01:11:28,111
As I told you on the phone, we
had an emergency exhumation.

742
01:11:28,612 --> 01:11:30,697
Please allow us to stay overnight.

743
01:11:33,283 --> 01:11:35,285
The mourner is on her way.

744
01:11:36,077 --> 01:11:38,580
Is there space to store the
coffin in the meantime?

745
01:11:58,516 --> 01:11:59,516
What...

746
01:12:00,267 --> 01:12:02,228
exactly is that?

747
01:12:04,438 --> 01:12:09,151
Could I trouble you for
some glutinous rice?

748
01:12:25,167 --> 01:12:26,043
Bong-gil.

749
01:12:26,085 --> 01:12:28,003
Get the horse blood from the car.

750
01:12:33,425 --> 01:12:35,136
You know this isn't a good thing.

751
01:12:40,599 --> 01:12:42,101
<i>Double interment?</i>

752
01:12:42,685 --> 01:12:44,270
<i>What does that mean?</i>

753
01:12:44,979 --> 01:12:48,399
<i>Please tell us everything you know.</i>

754
01:12:49,150 --> 01:12:50,317
<i>I don't know.</i>

755
01:12:50,985 --> 01:12:52,945
I really don't know...

756
01:12:55,072 --> 01:12:57,158
why that thing was buried there.

757
01:12:57,867 --> 01:13:02,329
Nor do I know why my father
was buried in such a bad plot.

758
01:13:03,247 --> 01:13:05,833
It was written on the tombstone.

759
01:13:06,959 --> 01:13:10,004
"Vice Chairman of the Central
Advisory Committee."

760
01:13:10,880 --> 01:13:15,384
Your father was quite a figure who
acted as a quisling for the country.

761
01:13:16,093 --> 01:13:19,180
So I'm assuming the monk
intended to punish him...

762
01:13:19,221 --> 01:13:20,514
Yes, I know.

763
01:13:22,224 --> 01:13:23,934
That's why I don't understand.

764
01:13:25,936 --> 01:13:27,897
That monk named Gisune...

765
01:13:30,107 --> 01:13:31,734
he wasn't Korean,

766
01:13:33,819 --> 01:13:34,987
but Japanese.

767
01:13:36,363 --> 01:13:38,157
- Pardon?
- A Japanese?

768
01:13:38,199 --> 01:13:41,243
His real name was Murayama Junji.

769
01:13:43,954 --> 01:13:48,125
I heard he knew every
inch of this country.

770
01:13:48,626 --> 01:13:51,295
My father pledged allegiance to them,

771
01:13:51,337 --> 01:13:55,382
so why bury him in the
worst plot in the country?

772
01:14:00,012 --> 01:14:03,140
I've received a call from
the US that the baby is fine.

773
01:14:03,891 --> 01:14:06,852
I'll honor the payment
Ji-yong promised you all,

774
01:14:07,645 --> 01:14:08,645
so please...

775
01:14:10,105 --> 01:14:11,941
get rid of that coffin as you see fit.

776
01:14:39,260 --> 01:14:40,553
Let's burn it right away.

777
01:14:42,763 --> 01:14:43,763
All right.

778
01:14:45,808 --> 01:14:48,102
Let's burn it first
thing in the morning.

779
01:14:48,144 --> 01:14:50,437
I agree. I'll feel so much better.

780
01:14:52,356 --> 01:14:53,356
Excuse me.

781
01:14:53,941 --> 01:14:57,027
I made some noodles,
so come warm up for a bit.

782
01:14:57,069 --> 01:14:58,571
Thank you.

783
01:14:58,612 --> 01:15:00,364
- Shall we?
- This way.

784
01:15:00,406 --> 01:15:04,118
I knew that grave was off. It
had a good view for nothing.

785
01:15:04,160 --> 01:15:05,995
We haven't eaten anything all day.

786
01:15:12,918 --> 01:15:15,796
Please have a drink of this.

787
01:15:15,838 --> 01:15:17,756
Thank you so much.

788
01:15:18,340 --> 01:15:20,217
Thank you for the food.

789
01:15:20,259 --> 01:15:21,927
- Cheers to our health.
- Cheers.

790
01:15:21,969 --> 01:15:23,637
The flavor is...

791
01:15:26,682 --> 01:15:29,018
This is really precious stuff.

792
01:15:29,059 --> 01:15:30,853
Have a drink.

793
01:15:30,895 --> 01:15:31,937
It's warming me up.

794
01:15:34,148 --> 01:15:35,316
Is there any more of the...

795
01:15:46,535 --> 01:15:48,662
Yes, Murayama Junji.

796
01:15:48,704 --> 01:15:53,250
<i>You don't remember? Master
mentioned him a few times.</i>

797
01:15:53,292 --> 01:15:56,712
<i>He was a Fox Diviner in Japan.</i>

798
01:15:57,963 --> 01:16:01,592
That's right, Diviner Murayama.

799
01:16:01,634 --> 01:16:04,512
<i>Master met him once a long time ago.</i>

800
01:16:04,553 --> 01:16:07,389
<i>I remember hearing that his energy
was too intense to be a human.</i>

801
01:16:07,431 --> 01:16:09,141
<i>That he was most certainly a fox.</i>

802
01:16:09,683 --> 01:16:10,810
<i>Why do you ask?</i>

803
01:16:10,851 --> 01:16:11,852
<i>Where are you?</i>

804
01:16:11,894 --> 01:16:14,688
It's nothing. I remember now.

805
01:16:15,272 --> 01:16:16,732
Thank you, Gwang-sim.

806
01:16:17,691 --> 01:16:18,943
I'll call back soon.

807
01:16:25,741 --> 01:16:26,951
Grandma.

808
01:16:28,619 --> 01:16:29,787
Grandma...

809
01:16:34,500 --> 01:16:36,252
I have a bad feeling.

810
01:17:34,602 --> 01:17:37,688
My liver was taken, my liver.

811
01:17:37,730 --> 01:17:38,814
My liver.

812
01:17:43,486 --> 01:17:45,529
My liver was taken.

813
01:17:45,571 --> 01:17:49,074
Someone took my liver.

814
01:17:49,116 --> 01:17:51,827
Someone took my liver. Someone took it.

815
01:17:51,869 --> 01:17:52,953
My liver was taken.

816
01:17:52,995 --> 01:17:55,122
Where are my clothes?

817
01:17:55,164 --> 01:17:57,124
My clothes.

818
01:17:58,793 --> 01:18:00,085
Fuck.

819
01:18:00,127 --> 01:18:03,005
Someone took my liver and my clothes.

820
01:18:03,047 --> 01:18:04,048
My liver.

821
01:19:57,661 --> 01:19:58,704
Hwa-rim.

822
01:20:14,136 --> 01:20:15,346
Damn it.

823
01:20:24,563 --> 01:20:25,981
Fuck, what a stench.

824
01:20:42,123 --> 01:20:44,375
It went through the
roof because of the seal.

825
01:20:48,671 --> 01:20:50,089
This thing...

826
01:20:52,842 --> 01:20:53,926
What the hell is it?

827
01:20:53,968 --> 01:20:54,968
Say it.

828
01:20:57,513 --> 01:21:01,225
I think this thing is at
the pigpen right now.

829
01:21:02,977 --> 01:21:04,353
Go and wake everyone up.

830
01:22:23,724 --> 01:22:25,976
The gate has been opened.

831
01:22:28,187 --> 01:22:29,772
Is there a human?

832
01:22:33,859 --> 01:22:36,862
I came for my helmet.

833
01:22:37,738 --> 01:22:39,198
Is there a human?

834
01:22:40,991 --> 01:22:45,996
No, my lord, I am not a human.

835
01:22:47,081 --> 01:22:49,542
I am your servant.

836
01:22:53,462 --> 01:22:55,005
Very well.

837
01:22:56,006 --> 01:23:00,052
Then have you brought me
the sweetfish and melons?

838
01:23:04,390 --> 01:23:08,144
Do you not hear your lord?

839
01:23:10,229 --> 01:23:13,649
I have brought the head
of the enemy general.

840
01:23:23,117 --> 01:23:24,827
I'm sorry, my lord.

841
01:23:26,078 --> 01:23:28,205
I will prepare the sweetfish for you.

842
01:23:56,484 --> 01:23:58,944
A human.

843
01:24:21,091 --> 01:24:22,092
Run.

844
01:24:22,843 --> 01:24:24,094
Bong-gil.

845
01:24:59,337 --> 01:25:00,338
Bong-gil.

846
01:25:20,817 --> 01:25:22,610
A pagoda.

847
01:27:32,740 --> 01:27:33,992
Bong-gil.

848
01:27:35,618 --> 01:27:36,494
Bong-gil!

849
01:27:36,536 --> 01:27:38,413
Bong-gil, stay with me.

850
01:27:40,206 --> 01:27:44,627
...350,000 won and 750,000
for Kim Young-ja...

851
01:27:44,669 --> 01:27:49,340
- Bong-gil, wake up!
- They owe me 200,000 won...

852
01:27:50,842 --> 01:27:52,385
Mr. Kim, please help!

853
01:27:53,052 --> 01:27:54,762
He needs help!

854
01:27:56,681 --> 01:27:58,766
Please help!

855
01:27:58,808 --> 01:28:00,185
He needs help.

856
01:28:00,852 --> 01:28:04,606
Bong-gil, stay with us.

857
01:28:17,035 --> 01:28:20,455
<i>A wild bear attack
terrorizing the villagers...</i>

858
01:28:20,497 --> 01:28:23,833
Your temperatures aren't dropping,
so I'll give you something for that.

859
01:28:23,875 --> 01:28:29,088
<i>The local police found pigs
that were shredded to pieces,</i>

860
01:28:29,130 --> 01:28:33,218
<i>as well as two human bodies in
the same condition near the scene.</i>

861
01:28:33,259 --> 01:28:38,431
<i>The victims were found to be a local monk
and a migrant laborer who worked on-site.</i>

862
01:28:38,473 --> 01:28:43,394
<i>Town officials are working in hand with
the military to track down the bear...</i>

863
01:29:13,174 --> 01:29:14,174
I'm sorry.

864
01:29:15,677 --> 01:29:17,971
I shouldn't have asked
to pull out the coffin.

865
01:29:19,514 --> 01:29:20,849
I'm sorry about Bong-gil...

866
01:29:23,309 --> 01:29:24,727
and the monk too.

867
01:29:26,938 --> 01:29:30,608
When Bong-gil had to quit baseball
after being chosen by the spirits...

868
01:29:33,486 --> 01:29:36,656
and when he came to us after
being abandoned by his family,

869
01:29:37,449 --> 01:29:39,909
we all told him not to become a shaman.

870
01:29:42,203 --> 01:29:44,247
But he said he'd be okay

871
01:29:44,289 --> 01:29:47,542
and that he had nothing to
fear as long as he was with me.

872
01:29:55,800 --> 01:29:57,677
I panicked, and I froze.

873
01:30:06,769 --> 01:30:08,104
It left footprints.

874
01:30:08,980 --> 01:30:10,356
And casted shadows too.

875
01:30:11,608 --> 01:30:14,736
There is an established
theory in shamanism.

876
01:30:15,778 --> 01:30:18,698
Souls are only fragmentary,
and ghosts lack physical bodies,

877
01:30:20,867 --> 01:30:24,287
meaning they can never
conquer us humans

878
01:30:24,329 --> 01:30:26,539
with complete minds and intact bodies.

879
01:30:27,832 --> 01:30:31,169
But that thing we saw is
something completely different.

880
01:30:32,253 --> 01:30:35,423
It's not a vengeful spirit
but rather an anima.

881
01:30:36,925 --> 01:30:37,842
An anima?

882
01:30:37,884 --> 01:30:39,302
It comes to be

883
01:30:39,344 --> 01:30:41,888
when a human or animal
soul evolves with an object.

884
01:30:44,015 --> 01:30:46,518
It's something that shouldn't
ever exist on this land.

885
01:30:50,563 --> 01:30:52,690
I couldn't sense anything from it.

886
01:30:54,067 --> 01:30:56,986
What its identity is,
where it came from,

887
01:30:58,029 --> 01:31:00,532
or why it was in the
Park family's grave...

888
01:31:06,121 --> 01:31:08,414
He suffered damage to
his abdominal organs.

889
01:31:09,165 --> 01:31:10,500
And he lost a lot of blood.

890
01:31:11,334 --> 01:31:14,045
But the real problem is
the damage to the spine.

891
01:31:14,963 --> 01:31:16,965
He needs to be sent
to a general hospital.

892
01:31:18,049 --> 01:31:19,801
Since it was a wild animal attack...

893
01:31:26,224 --> 01:31:28,226
<i>The Backbone of the Peninsula</i>

894
01:31:28,268 --> 01:31:29,727
<i>The Backbone</i>

895
01:31:29,769 --> 01:31:32,230
<i>The fox severed the tiger's waist.</i>

896
01:31:53,334 --> 01:31:55,054
<i>I was told they decided
on a nondescript one</i>

897
01:31:55,086 --> 01:31:57,088
<i>because of rampant grave
robberies at the time.</i>

898
01:31:57,130 --> 01:32:01,843
<i>The grave robbers' tools
are still stored in the shed.</i>

899
01:32:31,372 --> 01:32:34,626
"Our land, my comrades."

900
01:32:34,667 --> 01:32:35,919
"Iron Blood Alliance"?

901
01:32:42,217 --> 01:32:44,928
We've prevented further
organ damage for now

902
01:32:44,969 --> 01:32:48,348
and we'll need to conduct more tests,

903
01:32:48,389 --> 01:32:50,975
but he'll need to regain
consciousness for that.

904
01:32:51,976 --> 01:32:53,496
I must say, his case is quite unusual.

905
01:32:54,270 --> 01:32:56,397
What in the world is with all this?

906
01:32:56,439 --> 01:33:00,693
Thankfully, he's out of the
woods but he injured his spine.

907
01:33:00,735 --> 01:33:01,945
Will he be able to walk?

908
01:33:01,986 --> 01:33:04,948
He'll have to work through
it, which I'm sure he will.

909
01:33:07,075 --> 01:33:08,785
What have you been up to?

910
01:33:08,827 --> 01:33:10,161
Spill it.

911
01:33:11,371 --> 01:33:13,206
- Gwang-sim.
- Yes?

912
01:33:13,248 --> 01:33:14,916
I smell a stench from him.

913
01:33:17,919 --> 01:33:19,963
I know. That's why I called you two.

914
01:33:20,755 --> 01:33:22,924
It's been a while since we
played goblins, hasn't it?

915
01:33:24,843 --> 01:33:26,302
Why are you standing around, Ja-hye?

916
01:33:26,845 --> 01:33:27,845
Go lock the door.

917
01:33:37,021 --> 01:33:40,608
<i>Bae Ji-dang, Lee Chung-gu,</i>

918
01:33:40,650 --> 01:33:44,445
<i>Park Gil-ho, Shin Pal-gyun,</i>

919
01:33:45,738 --> 01:33:49,576
<i>Kim Jung-bok, Song Jong-ik,</i>

920
01:33:50,118 --> 01:33:53,329
Min Geun-ho,

921
01:33:53,371 --> 01:33:56,416
Jeon Tae-hwan, and Im Chung-sin.

922
01:33:57,792 --> 01:33:58,793
I knew it.

923
01:33:59,461 --> 01:34:03,006
They look too resolute
to be grave robbers.

924
01:34:31,701 --> 01:34:34,871
Ladies, it's been so long.

925
01:34:35,413 --> 01:34:36,706
Is everyone here?

926
01:34:36,748 --> 01:34:38,458
I just got here.

927
01:34:38,500 --> 01:34:41,920
The harvest is over, and
it's getting cold now.

928
01:34:41,961 --> 01:34:43,171
Is everyone well?

929
01:34:43,213 --> 01:34:48,051
With you all here, I should've
cooked something.

930
01:34:48,092 --> 01:34:49,844
Don't you worry.

931
01:34:49,886 --> 01:34:53,973
I brought rice cakes
and plenty of boiled pork.

932
01:34:54,015 --> 01:34:57,560
I knew I smelled something tasty.

933
01:34:57,602 --> 01:34:59,103
Did you bring enough?

934
01:34:59,145 --> 01:35:01,689
Of course, I brought plenty.

935
01:35:01,731 --> 01:35:03,983
There's more than
enough for all three of us.

936
01:35:04,025 --> 01:35:07,904
Should I get Mr. Jang over yonder
and the miss over at Jecheon too?

937
01:35:07,946 --> 01:35:09,906
Why fetch those busy bees?

938
01:35:09,948 --> 01:35:12,075
Let's just eat quietly by ourselves...

939
01:35:12,117 --> 01:35:16,496
Yes, let's not bring others.
Did you bring some sweetfish?

940
01:35:22,377 --> 01:35:23,294
Who's that?

941
01:35:23,336 --> 01:35:27,757
- I think Mr. Yoon is here.
- No way.

942
01:35:27,799 --> 01:35:29,342
Didn't you hear what happened to him?

943
01:35:29,384 --> 01:35:33,179
Yes, there's no way he came.

944
01:35:33,221 --> 01:35:36,099
What are you talking about?
Fill me in, will you?

945
01:35:36,141 --> 01:35:37,517
Don't even mention it.

946
01:35:38,685 --> 01:35:41,312
I heard he met something
really vicious.

947
01:35:41,354 --> 01:35:46,109
How vicious was it for
him to be bedridden?

948
01:35:46,151 --> 01:35:47,151
Haven't you heard?

949
01:35:48,444 --> 01:35:50,613
He met someone in
the middle of the night.

950
01:35:52,449 --> 01:35:54,451
What a load of shit.

951
01:35:56,077 --> 01:35:57,912
Hey, Mr. Yoon.

952
01:35:58,955 --> 01:36:01,374
What did you see that scared you much?

953
01:36:04,043 --> 01:36:06,296
He looks just fine.

954
01:36:07,338 --> 01:36:08,548
Who was it?

955
01:36:09,799 --> 01:36:11,634
The one you met.

956
01:36:12,594 --> 01:36:14,053
Can you tell us?

957
01:36:16,848 --> 01:36:19,809
The lord.

958
01:36:21,102 --> 01:36:22,102
The lord?

959
01:36:23,354 --> 01:36:24,647
Which one?

960
01:36:31,362 --> 01:36:34,365
Spit it out, asshole.

961
01:36:41,998 --> 01:36:46,419
My lord, the one who
cut down 10,000 foes.

962
01:36:51,382 --> 01:36:52,759
Where...

963
01:36:54,469 --> 01:36:56,221
is your lord now?

964
01:37:17,617 --> 01:37:20,829
38.3417, 128.3189.

965
01:37:20,870 --> 01:37:24,457
38.3417, 128.3189.

966
01:37:25,500 --> 01:37:28,920
38.3417, 128.3189.

967
01:37:30,797 --> 01:37:32,215
It's a Japanese ghost.

968
01:37:33,675 --> 01:37:38,303
He's the general who guards the site.

969
01:37:54,611 --> 01:37:56,238
What the hell is that?

970
01:37:58,949 --> 01:38:01,577
My lord, please look at me!

971
01:38:02,536 --> 01:38:04,663
I'm right here.

972
01:38:04,705 --> 01:38:06,415
I wish to be your vessel!

973
01:38:21,763 --> 01:38:24,641
I'll offer him that meat.

974
01:38:26,351 --> 01:38:27,478
Ja-hye.

975
01:38:28,520 --> 01:38:29,730
Come closer.

976
01:38:30,522 --> 01:38:32,399
Please help me, Ja-hye.

977
01:38:39,114 --> 01:38:43,327
All of you bitches are going to die.

978
01:38:56,840 --> 01:38:58,592
Don't do this, Hwa-rim.

979
01:38:58,634 --> 01:39:00,052
It's a Japanese ghost.

980
01:39:00,093 --> 01:39:01,512
I know.

981
01:39:01,553 --> 01:39:06,391
They kill anything and everything
just for being nearby.

982
01:39:07,851 --> 01:39:09,520
You saw what happened in Japan.

983
01:39:09,561 --> 01:39:11,897
Don't you dare even go near it.

984
01:39:13,232 --> 01:39:17,820
Even with your grandma
protecting you, this isn't right.

985
01:39:18,320 --> 01:39:19,363
Let's go, Ja-hye.

986
01:39:19,905 --> 01:39:21,365
What about Bong-gil then?

987
01:39:24,535 --> 01:39:26,411
I'll call you. Let's go.

988
01:39:41,885 --> 01:39:43,637
So that thing was
really buried down there?

989
01:39:45,347 --> 01:39:47,432
That means it's
returned to where it was.

990
01:39:48,767 --> 01:39:51,353
But why did you go back
there in the first place?

991
01:39:53,564 --> 01:39:56,066
Before Mr. Park died, he said,

992
01:39:58,026 --> 01:40:00,904
"The fox severed the tiger's waist."

993
01:40:02,656 --> 01:40:04,074
What does it mean?

994
01:40:04,116 --> 01:40:08,454
In geomancy, our peninsula is
metaphorically compared to a tiger,

995
01:40:09,580 --> 01:40:11,707
one that is grasping the continent.

996
01:40:12,291 --> 01:40:13,167
So?

997
01:40:13,208 --> 01:40:16,920
Remember the coordinates
written on the gravestone?

998
01:40:16,962 --> 01:40:18,422
Where could it be?

999
01:40:18,464 --> 01:40:20,507
That's right, that's the spot.

1000
01:40:20,549 --> 01:40:22,551
That's exactly where
the tiger's waist is.

1001
01:40:22,593 --> 01:40:25,262
That Fox Diviner Hwa-rim mentioned,

1002
01:40:26,221 --> 01:40:27,764
that fox bastard...

1003
01:40:29,266 --> 01:40:31,351
put it there just like that!

1004
01:40:31,393 --> 01:40:33,604
He drove a stake right on the spot.

1005
01:40:38,525 --> 01:40:40,944
What about Park's coffin on top of it?

1006
01:40:43,280 --> 01:40:47,618
Since these resolute-looking men
were roaming about pulling them out,

1007
01:40:47,659 --> 01:40:50,370
they intentionally buried a
high-ranking official on top of it.

1008
01:40:50,412 --> 01:40:52,039
So that they couldn't even go near it.

1009
01:40:52,080 --> 01:40:54,374
Then why is the ghost there?

1010
01:40:59,004 --> 01:41:04,051
He's the general who guards the site.

1011
01:41:08,931 --> 01:41:12,768
38.3417, 128.3189.

1012
01:41:13,519 --> 01:41:14,770
I think...

1013
01:41:15,771 --> 01:41:17,815
that's what's guarding the iron stake.

1014
01:41:32,496 --> 01:41:33,580
Hwa-rim.

1015
01:41:34,081 --> 01:41:36,583
I know we're based on
a business relationship,

1016
01:41:37,793 --> 01:41:39,753
but let me ask you a
favor aside from business.

1017
01:41:39,795 --> 01:41:41,922
Don't say anything you'll regret later.

1018
01:41:41,964 --> 01:41:43,423
Do you still believe

1019
01:41:43,465 --> 01:41:47,261
in national spirit, or how Korea was
divided in half with iron stakes?

1020
01:41:47,302 --> 01:41:51,348
You know those stakes at the
temples are for land surveying.

1021
01:41:51,390 --> 01:41:54,518
You know they say 99% of them are fake.

1022
01:41:54,560 --> 01:41:55,560
What about the 1% then?

1023
01:41:57,688 --> 01:41:59,731
- Mr. Ko.
- What is it?

1024
01:41:59,773 --> 01:42:02,151
You know this isn't
just an ordinary grave.

1025
01:42:02,192 --> 01:42:04,153
This was planned meticulously.

1026
01:42:05,821 --> 01:42:09,324
You saw people die
because of that grave.

1027
01:42:09,366 --> 01:42:11,285
Do you really want to be next?

1028
01:42:11,326 --> 01:42:12,327
Mr. Kim.

1029
01:42:12,369 --> 01:42:17,583
Stake or not, we lived our lives
just fine without big trouble.

1030
01:42:17,624 --> 01:42:19,501
So why the change of heart?

1031
01:42:19,543 --> 01:42:20,543
You're right.

1032
01:42:21,295 --> 01:42:26,341
You and I lived prosperously,
selling land to rich pricks.

1033
01:42:27,050 --> 01:42:28,427
That's what bothers me.

1034
01:42:28,469 --> 01:42:30,429
This is about that same land!

1035
01:42:32,222 --> 01:42:35,559
The land that my unborn
grandchild will step on and live on.

1036
01:42:35,601 --> 01:42:38,353
The same land for all of us

1037
01:42:38,395 --> 01:42:40,147
and our future generations.

1038
01:42:43,901 --> 01:42:46,445
Hwa-rim, you said it's an anima.

1039
01:42:46,487 --> 01:42:49,072
If it really is an anima
attached to the iron,

1040
01:42:49,114 --> 01:42:51,617
we just have to pull
out that iron stake.

1041
01:42:51,658 --> 01:42:54,495
With that done, Bong-gil
will recover, no?

1042
01:43:00,250 --> 01:43:03,879
But that general or
whatever is guarding it.

1043
01:43:03,921 --> 01:43:06,131
How the hell are we
supposed to pull it out?

1044
01:43:06,173 --> 01:43:08,801
You saw the size of that thing.

1045
01:43:10,677 --> 01:43:12,763
<i>Summon like a beast,</i>

1046
01:43:15,057 --> 01:43:16,809
<i>speak like an anima.</i>

1047
01:43:20,020 --> 01:43:21,939
You really think it's doable?

1048
01:43:21,980 --> 01:43:24,525
There are things we can
pull off and things we can't.

1049
01:43:24,566 --> 01:43:25,984
I'm sorry to say that ghost

1050
01:43:26,985 --> 01:43:28,529
isn't something that can be cast away.

1051
01:43:29,613 --> 01:43:35,285
Japanese ghosts don't need a
reason to kill anything in their path.

1052
01:43:37,204 --> 01:43:39,998
We may not be able to get rid of it,

1053
01:43:43,210 --> 01:43:44,795
but I can distract it for a bit.

1054
01:43:46,588 --> 01:43:48,549
I can buy us time.

1055
01:43:57,599 --> 01:43:58,809
Bong-gil.

1056
01:44:01,895 --> 01:44:04,481
Pass me some more antiseptic, please.

1057
01:44:04,523 --> 01:44:06,692
I'll wipe it with saline
and apply gauze over it.

1058
01:44:07,276 --> 01:44:08,276
Yes, ma'am.

1059
01:44:08,944 --> 01:44:10,028
Wait.

1060
01:44:15,325 --> 01:44:17,244
That bastard avoided the tattoo.

1061
01:44:18,370 --> 01:44:19,955
What kind of tattoo is that?

1062
01:44:21,248 --> 01:44:22,624
It's a Buddhist scripture.

1063
01:44:47,858 --> 01:44:49,026
My apologies,

1064
01:44:49,860 --> 01:44:52,488
but we had some reports of wild
animal activities in the area.

1065
01:44:55,073 --> 01:44:56,158
Where...

1066
01:44:57,159 --> 01:44:58,494
Where might you...

1067
01:44:59,620 --> 01:45:01,663
be headed?

1068
01:45:02,706 --> 01:45:07,169
We're here to weed out
graves in that mountain.

1069
01:45:07,753 --> 01:45:08,753
I see.

1070
01:45:09,254 --> 01:45:13,592
The soldiers are conducting a
search starting with that mountain.

1071
01:45:13,634 --> 01:45:18,055
We'll finish quickly and
come back down soon.

1072
01:45:18,096 --> 01:45:19,096
Very well.

1073
01:45:19,515 --> 01:45:20,515
Let them through.

1074
01:46:17,489 --> 01:46:19,950
<i>Pull out and return to base.</i>

1075
01:46:19,992 --> 01:46:23,787
We gave it what it wanted, so I
suppose it'll wake up at midnight.

1076
01:46:24,997 --> 01:46:30,127
If you can lure it to the yew tree,
I'll buy us as much time as I can.

1077
01:46:30,752 --> 01:46:33,422
It won't take us long to pull it out.

1078
01:46:33,464 --> 01:46:35,883
Just get us 30 minutes.

1079
01:46:35,924 --> 01:46:38,302
When you pull out the iron stake...

1080
01:46:41,430 --> 01:46:43,932
make sure to cleanse it
immediately with this horse blood.

1081
01:46:46,560 --> 01:46:47,560
Mr. Kim.

1082
01:46:48,645 --> 01:46:49,813
You're sure that iron stake

1083
01:46:51,482 --> 01:46:52,858
is really there, right?

1084
01:46:56,445 --> 01:46:57,613
I'm absolutely certain.

1085
01:47:05,954 --> 01:47:08,415
Gwang-sim, please
look after Bong-gil tonight.

1086
01:47:08,916 --> 01:47:11,627
If things go wrong, he'll be in danger.

1087
01:47:33,023 --> 01:47:34,107
Stop staring.

1088
01:47:34,608 --> 01:47:36,151
She said it'll show up at midnight.

1089
01:47:49,331 --> 01:47:50,331
Mr. Ko.

1090
01:47:51,792 --> 01:47:53,752
Thanks for coming with me.

1091
01:47:53,794 --> 01:47:55,671
"A person alone can be
attacked and defeated,

1092
01:47:55,712 --> 01:47:58,006
but two can stand
back-to-back and conquer."

1093
01:47:58,048 --> 01:47:59,049
"Three are even better,

1094
01:47:59,091 --> 01:48:00,971
for a triple-braided cord
is not easily broken."

1095
01:48:01,468 --> 01:48:03,095
Ecclesiastes 4:12.

1096
01:48:05,931 --> 01:48:06,932
Amen.

1097
01:48:24,199 --> 01:48:25,199
Gwang-sim.

1098
01:48:26,577 --> 01:48:28,620
I hope we won't have to kill it.

1099
01:48:30,080 --> 01:48:31,915
It would be dying in his place.

1100
01:48:34,376 --> 01:48:37,421
Plus, you like fried chicken,
so what's the matter?

1101
01:51:38,643 --> 01:51:40,812
Have you filled your stomach?

1102
01:51:58,579 --> 01:51:59,747
It has to be here.

1103
01:52:11,801 --> 01:52:14,137
Is someone there?

1104
01:52:19,225 --> 01:52:21,519
My mountain is being disturbed.

1105
01:52:26,357 --> 01:52:30,027
Does this mountain belong to you?

1106
01:52:32,530 --> 01:52:35,741
Indeed, this is my mountain.

1107
01:52:36,534 --> 01:52:39,787
Goddamn old tree god.

1108
01:52:40,788 --> 01:52:44,959
How is it that I do not hear
any guns or bayonets?

1109
01:52:45,668 --> 01:52:47,170
You are mistaken.

1110
01:52:48,880 --> 01:52:50,590
The war ended a long time ago...

1111
01:52:50,631 --> 01:52:51,631
No!

1112
01:52:52,383 --> 01:52:54,802
Our war has not ended yet!

1113
01:53:07,273 --> 01:53:11,527
Why have you come here?

1114
01:53:14,113 --> 01:53:19,619
That fox brought me
here on the battlefield

1115
01:53:19,660 --> 01:53:24,624
instead of the Namsan shrine
when I was kept in Daitoku-ji.

1116
01:53:26,417 --> 01:53:29,545
I assume it was under Katahito's order.

1117
01:53:29,587 --> 01:53:32,799
Or that of Makoto's.

1118
01:53:40,848 --> 01:53:42,892
This is a quaint land now.

1119
01:53:43,476 --> 01:53:45,645
You do not belong here anymore.

1120
01:53:49,607 --> 01:53:52,276
No, no.

1121
01:53:52,318 --> 01:53:56,072
We must continue heading North.

1122
01:53:56,114 --> 01:53:59,283
- Raise your bayonets and head North!
- And head North!

1123
01:53:59,325 --> 01:54:01,869
- Head North!
- Head North!

1124
01:54:01,911 --> 01:54:05,706
- A brave warrior never retreats.
- A brave warrior never retreats.

1125
01:54:14,132 --> 01:54:15,133
I don't understand.

1126
01:54:15,174 --> 01:54:16,467
There's nothing here.

1127
01:54:21,764 --> 01:54:24,183
As the ruler of this
place, I will ask again.

1128
01:54:25,017 --> 01:54:27,353
Since when have you been here?

1129
01:54:28,437 --> 01:54:30,356
Retain your respect for me!

1130
01:54:31,399 --> 01:54:36,154
I am the embodiment of fear.

1131
01:54:36,195 --> 01:54:37,780
This is my land!

1132
01:54:37,822 --> 01:54:38,823
I will ask again.

1133
01:54:38,865 --> 01:54:40,116
What are you?

1134
01:54:47,373 --> 01:54:48,624
It's not here.

1135
01:54:48,666 --> 01:54:49,667
It's not here!

1136
01:54:52,003 --> 01:54:53,171
There's nothing here.

1137
01:54:53,212 --> 01:54:54,252
You said you were certain!

1138
01:55:02,847 --> 01:55:05,349
It has to be here.

1139
01:55:05,933 --> 01:55:07,602
Remember.

1140
01:55:08,936 --> 01:55:15,776
They took my head at Sekigahara,
but I transcended the mortal form.

1141
01:55:15,818 --> 01:55:18,321
I am the god of the battlefield.

1142
01:55:18,362 --> 01:55:22,742
My undecaying lord,
you are a burning sword!

1143
01:55:23,451 --> 01:55:26,954
38.3417, 128.3189.

1144
01:55:26,996 --> 01:55:29,749
The fox has put a curse on me.

1145
01:55:29,791 --> 01:55:32,460
I must protect this site.

1146
01:55:45,097 --> 01:55:47,892
Do you have someone captive?

1147
01:55:49,769 --> 01:55:53,064
Please free the human you hold captive.

1148
01:55:54,232 --> 01:55:55,232
Now!

1149
01:55:55,983 --> 01:55:57,235
I beg of you!

1150
01:56:06,661 --> 01:56:07,995
A human.

1151
01:56:09,038 --> 01:56:10,289
Forward.

1152
01:56:11,791 --> 01:56:13,334
Forward.

1153
01:56:14,293 --> 01:56:15,670
Forward.

1154
01:56:17,755 --> 01:56:19,173
Forward.

1155
01:56:29,308 --> 01:56:31,352
Cursed old hag.

1156
01:57:02,800 --> 01:57:03,676
Did you find it?

1157
01:57:03,718 --> 01:57:05,845
- There's nothing there.
- What do you mean?

1158
01:57:05,887 --> 01:57:07,807
We couldn't find anything.
We have to pull out...

1159
01:57:25,239 --> 01:57:26,324
Mr. Kim.

1160
01:57:30,203 --> 01:57:32,163
This can't be.

1161
01:57:33,790 --> 01:57:35,875
It has to be here somewhere.

1162
01:57:45,009 --> 01:57:48,346
38.3417, 128.3189.

1163
01:57:48,387 --> 01:57:51,891
My lord, please return.

1164
01:57:51,933 --> 01:57:55,436
38.3417, 128.3189!

1165
01:57:56,103 --> 01:57:57,396
Kim Sang-duk!

1166
01:58:10,451 --> 01:58:13,162
Mr. Kim! Get out of there!

1167
01:58:26,509 --> 01:58:28,553
<i>Then why is the ghost there?</i>

1168
01:58:28,594 --> 01:58:30,429
<i>He said he's the general
guarding the site.</i>

1169
01:58:30,471 --> 01:58:32,348
<i>That means it's
returned to where it was.</i>

1170
01:58:32,390 --> 01:58:34,725
<i>Have you ever seen a
coffin buried vertically?</i>

1171
01:58:38,896 --> 01:58:40,273
<i>Fire.</i>

1172
01:58:41,190 --> 01:58:44,318
<i>The fire digs into the ground.</i>

1173
01:58:45,361 --> 01:58:46,361
Get out!

1174
01:59:01,794 --> 01:59:03,629
Will you become my servant?

1175
01:59:06,215 --> 01:59:07,675
If not,

1176
01:59:08,676 --> 01:59:10,761
will you offer your liver to me?

1177
01:59:15,224 --> 01:59:19,312
It has been over 500 years
since I memorized...

1178
01:59:20,897 --> 01:59:22,815
the scripture written on you.

1179
01:59:25,902 --> 01:59:27,945
<i>The metal driven into the ground,</i>

1180
01:59:29,489 --> 01:59:31,574
<i>and the fire that guards it.</i>

1181
01:59:32,450 --> 01:59:33,993
Devour...

1182
01:59:35,620 --> 01:59:36,954
the liver, my lord.

1183
01:59:38,206 --> 01:59:39,957
A fresh liver.

1184
01:59:46,798 --> 01:59:48,257
The horse blood!

1185
02:00:02,271 --> 02:00:04,065
The blood of the white horse.

1186
02:00:05,775 --> 02:00:06,859
It's hot.

1187
02:00:12,406 --> 02:00:14,158
Please retreat.

1188
02:00:15,034 --> 02:00:18,704
You cannot have them find you again.

1189
02:00:22,083 --> 02:00:23,209
<i>It's an anima.</i>

1190
02:00:24,168 --> 02:00:25,795
It comes to be

1191
02:00:26,838 --> 02:00:29,215
when a human or animal
soul evolves with an object.

1192
02:00:31,884 --> 02:00:34,303
<i>Yes, it's the iron.</i>

1193
02:00:36,305 --> 02:00:39,433
<i>You are the burning metal.</i>

1194
02:00:46,107 --> 02:00:48,192
Mr. Kim.

1195
02:00:48,234 --> 02:00:49,234
Pull yourself together!

1196
02:00:49,569 --> 02:00:50,849
Hurry, we have to carry him out.

1197
02:01:50,087 --> 02:01:51,297
<i>Earth...</i>

1198
02:01:53,883 --> 02:01:55,676
<i>and wood.</i>

1199
02:01:56,636 --> 02:02:00,932
<i>Based on the energy of the earth,
fire, water, wood, and metal</i>

1200
02:02:01,432 --> 02:02:03,100
<i>form the four cardinal directions.</i>

1201
02:02:08,523 --> 02:02:10,983
<i>Fire and water are opposite poles,</i>

1202
02:02:11,734 --> 02:02:14,612
<i>and so are metal and wood.</i>

1203
02:02:23,454 --> 02:02:24,454
<i>That's it.</i>

1204
02:02:43,516 --> 02:02:45,226
<i>Burning metal.</i>

1205
02:02:47,687 --> 02:02:49,272
<i>The opposite of that...</i>

1206
02:02:50,690 --> 02:02:52,692
<i>is wet wood.</i>

1207
02:03:02,910 --> 02:03:05,288
<i>Water conquers fire...</i>

1208
02:03:13,463 --> 02:03:15,047
<i>and wet wood...</i>

1209
02:03:17,800 --> 02:03:19,426
<i>is tougher than metal.</i>

1210
02:03:35,609 --> 02:03:36,609
Gwang-sim, wait.

1211
02:03:37,486 --> 02:03:38,653
His blood is dark.

1212
02:04:00,759 --> 02:04:03,512
<i>One last blow.</i>

1213
02:04:48,682 --> 02:04:50,058
Are you okay, Bong-gil?

1214
02:04:57,649 --> 02:04:58,567
Mr. Kim.

1215
02:04:58,608 --> 02:05:00,360
What do we do?

1216
02:05:00,402 --> 02:05:01,903
- Mr. Kim.
- What do we do?

1217
02:05:02,612 --> 02:05:03,947
What do we...

1218
02:05:06,366 --> 02:05:07,659
<i>I'm dying.</i>

1219
02:05:08,952 --> 02:05:11,163
<i>Thankfully, it's not that painful.</i>

1220
02:05:11,705 --> 02:05:13,415
Hey, Kim Sang-duk!

1221
02:05:13,457 --> 02:05:15,041
Don't die on me!

1222
02:05:15,083 --> 02:05:17,586
<i>I've always lived so close to death.</i>

1223
02:05:20,422 --> 02:05:25,302
<i>I guess it's just my turn now.</i>

1224
02:05:28,013 --> 02:05:30,765
<i>Dying is about returning to earth.</i>

1225
02:05:32,893 --> 02:05:34,728
<i>I'll leave in comfort...</i>

1226
02:05:36,688 --> 02:05:40,484
<i>Wait, my daughter's wedding...</i>

1227
02:05:40,525 --> 02:05:43,445
Grant him the courage
to overcome the surgery.

1228
02:05:43,487 --> 02:05:46,114
Lord, please envelope him
with your precious blood.

1229
02:05:56,082 --> 02:06:00,295
<i>Several people died, and a few
others were injured over a few days.</i>

1230
02:06:00,796 --> 02:06:02,964
<i>Upon inspection of security cameras...</i>

1231
02:06:03,006 --> 02:06:08,637
<i>After several days of searching,
the soldiers captured a wild bear,</i>

1232
02:06:09,930 --> 02:06:14,434
<i>and the media is on an ongoing debate
on whether to kill this innocent bear.</i>

1233
02:06:16,520 --> 02:06:19,397
<i>For the safety of the villagers...</i>

1234
02:06:21,233 --> 02:06:22,233
He's awake.

1235
02:06:23,902 --> 02:06:24,903
Mr. Kim.

1236
02:06:25,821 --> 02:06:27,989
Are you awake?

1237
02:06:28,031 --> 02:06:32,410
<i>Thankfully, Mr. Kim's recovery
was rapid despite his age.</i>

1238
02:06:33,912 --> 02:06:35,497
<i>As for Bong-gil,</i>

1239
02:06:36,414 --> 02:06:37,290
<i>well...</i>

1240
02:06:37,332 --> 02:06:39,084
Speak of the devil.

1241
02:06:39,751 --> 02:06:41,503
Seriously?

1242
02:06:42,462 --> 02:06:43,588
This is our meal.

1243
02:06:43,630 --> 02:06:45,006
How could you eat without me?

1244
02:06:45,048 --> 02:06:46,967
- Here, eat.
- Give me a slice.

1245
02:06:59,729 --> 02:07:01,731
Is this a diner?

1246
02:07:01,773 --> 02:07:03,900
Why are you all always eating here?

1247
02:07:03,942 --> 02:07:05,819
You think I'm eating because I want to?

1248
02:07:05,861 --> 02:07:08,029
I'm stuffing myself
because it's so good.

1249
02:07:08,071 --> 02:07:09,281
It's good.

1250
02:07:09,322 --> 02:07:12,576
You have to fast, so
someone's got to eat these.

1251
02:07:13,326 --> 02:07:15,036
Think of it as a diet.

1252
02:07:22,752 --> 02:07:26,882
<i>Winter passed and we
all went back to our lives...</i>

1253
02:07:29,301 --> 02:07:30,760
<i>as if nothing had happened.</i>

1254
02:07:55,327 --> 02:08:00,415
♪ - While I live briefly in this world, ♪
♪ - While I live briefly in this world, ♪

1255
02:08:00,457 --> 02:08:05,378
♪ - Always singing praises ♪
♪ - Always singing praises ♪

1256
02:08:05,921 --> 02:08:11,468
♪ - When the day fades away, ♪
♪ - When the day fades away, ♪

1257
02:08:11,510 --> 02:08:16,848
♪ - I shall proceed in glory ♪
♪ - I shall proceed in glory ♪

1258
02:08:16,890 --> 02:08:18,576
♪ - Through the gate of heaven... ♪
♪ - Through the gate of heaven... ♪

1259
02:08:18,600 --> 02:08:21,812
I told you it has to face
the West, did I not?

1260
02:08:21,853 --> 02:08:24,815
Facing the South isn't
always a good thing.

1261
02:08:25,524 --> 02:08:27,400
What should we do then?

1262
02:08:37,410 --> 02:08:40,455
The bride and groom will
now bow to each other.

1263
02:08:41,498 --> 02:08:43,416
Bride and groom, please bow.

1264
02:08:54,136 --> 02:08:58,849
Family members, please step
forward for a group picture.

1265
02:08:58,890 --> 02:09:00,308
Hey, Mr. Ko.

1266
02:09:01,518 --> 02:09:02,853
Get over here.

1267
02:09:03,895 --> 02:09:06,773
It's a family photo. Why
would we be included?

1268
02:09:09,234 --> 02:09:11,153
Let's just join for one photo.

1269
02:09:11,194 --> 02:09:12,821
Let's just take one.

1270
02:09:12,863 --> 02:09:14,340
- We're practically family.
- Let's go.

1271
02:09:14,364 --> 02:09:16,283
But it's a family photo.

1272
02:09:19,411 --> 02:09:22,706
The tall gentleman in the
middle, please take a step up.

1273
02:09:22,747 --> 02:09:25,959
The gentleman in glasses,
please come closer.

1274
02:09:27,169 --> 02:09:28,170
Make sure you don't...

1275
02:09:28,211 --> 02:09:31,423
How do we have
bellies of the same size?

1276
02:09:31,465 --> 02:09:32,757
Goodness.

1277
02:09:32,799 --> 02:09:34,176
